name: AnalyserNode
description: The AnalyserNode interface represents a node able to provide real-time frequency and time-domain analysis information. It is an AudioNode that passes the audio stream unchanged from the input to the output. It has exactly one input and one output. The node works even if the output is not connected.

properties.name: AnalyserNode.fftSize
properties.description: Is an unsigned long value representing the size of the Fast Fourier Transform to be used to determine the frequency domain. It must be a non-zero power of 2 in the range between 32 and 2048, included; its default value is 2048. If not a power of 2, or outside the specified range, the exception INDEX_SIZE_ERR is thrown.

properties.name: AnalyserNode.frequencyBinCount
properties.description: Is an unsigned long value containing half the FFT size.

properties.name: AnalyserNode.minDecibels
properties.description: Is a double value representing the minimum power value in the scaling range for the FFT analysis data for conversion to unsigned bytw values. If a value greater than AnalyserNode.maxDecibels is set, an INDEX_SIZE_ERR exception is thrown. It defaults to -100.

properties.name: AnalyserNode.maxDecibels
properties.description: Is a double value representing the maximumum power value in the scaling range for the FFT analysis data for conversion to unsigned bytw values. If a value smaller than AnalyserNode.minDecibels is set, an INDEX_SIZE_ERR exception is thrown. It defaults to -30.

properties.name: AnalyserNode.smoothingTimeConstant
properties.description: Is a double value representing the averaging constant with the last analysis frame. It must be between 0 and 1, included and defaults to 0.8 (and 0 meaning no time averaging). If outside this range, an INDEX_SIZE_ERR exception is thrown

name: AnimationEvent
description: AnimationEvent objects provide information about events that occur related to CSS animations.

properties.name: target
properties.description: The event target (the topmost target in the DOM tree).

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of event.

properties.name: canBubble
properties.description: Does the event normally bubble?

properties.name: cancelable
properties.description: Is it possible to cancel the event?

properties.name: animationName
properties.description: The name of the CSS property associated with the transition. Read only.

properties.name: elapsedTime
properties.description: The amount of time the animation has been running, in seconds, when this event fired, excluding any time the animation was paused. For an "animationstart" event, the elapsedTime is zero unless there was a negative value for animation-delay, in which case the event will be fired with an elapsedTime of (-1 * delay). Read only.

name: App
description: In the Open Web apps JavaScript API, an App object is a JavaScript object that represents an app that is or could be installed in the user's app repository.

properties.name: manifest
properties.description: The currently stored instance of the manifest of the app.

properties.name: manifestURL
properties.description: Where the manifest was found.

properties.name: origin
properties.description: The origin of the app (protocol, host, and optional port number). For example: http://example.com

properties.name: installOrigin
properties.description: The origin of the site that triggered the installation of the app.

properties.name: installTime
properties.description: The time that the app was installed. This is generated using Date().getTime(), represented as the number of milliseconds since midnight of January 1st, 1970.

properties.name: receipts
properties.description: An object containing an array of one or more receipts. Each receipt is a string. If there are no receipts, this is null.

name: Apps
description: Provides support for installing, managing, and controlling Open Web apps in a browser. Currently implemented as window.navigator.mozApps.

properties.name: mgmt
properties.description: A mgmt object that exposes functions that let dashboards manage and launch apps on a user's behalf.

name: Attr
description: This type represents a DOM element's attribute as an object. In most DOM methods, you will probably directly retrieve the attribute as a string (e.g., Element.getAttribute(), but certain functions (e.g., Element.getAttributeNode()) or means of iterating give Attr types.

properties.name: isId
properties.description: Indicates whether the attribute is an "ID attribute". An "ID attribute" being an attribute which value is expected to be unique across a DOM Document. In HTML DOM, "id" is the only ID attribute, but XML documents could define others. Whether or not an attribute is unique is often determined by a DTD or other schema description.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The attribute's name.

properties.name: ownerElement
properties.description: This property has been deprecated and will be removed in the future. Since you can only get Attr objects from elements, you should already know the owner.

properties.name: schemaTypeInfo
properties.description: ?

properties.name: specified
properties.description: This property has been deprecated and will be removed in the future; it now always returns true. Originally, it returned true if the attribute was explicitly specified in the source code or by a script, and false if its value came from the default one defined in the document's DTD.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The attribute's value.

name: AudioBuffer
description: {{WebAudioRef}}

properties.name: AudioBuffer.sampleRate
properties.description: Returns a float representing the sample rate, samples per second, of the PCM data stored in the buffer.

properties.name: AudioBuffer.length
properties.description: Returns an integer representing the length, in sample-frames, of the PCM data stored in the buffer.

properties.name: AudioBuffer.duration
properties.description: Returns a double representing the duration, in seconds, of the PCM data stored in the buffer.

properties.name: AudioBuffer.numberOfChannels
properties.description: Returns an integer representing the number of discrete audio channels described by the PCM data stored in the buffer.

name: AudioBufferSourceNode
description: The AudioBufferSourceNode interface represents an audio source consisting of in-memory audio data, stored in an . It is an  that acts as an audio source; AudioBufferSourceNode has no input and exactly one output. The amount of channels in the output corresponds to tha amount of channels of the  contained in the AudioBufferSourceNode.buffer attribute. If there is no buffer set, that is if the attribute's value is NULL, the output contains one single channel consisting of silence.

properties.name: AudioBufferSourceNode.buffer
properties.description: Is an AudioNode, or the value NULL, that defines the audio asset to be played.

properties.name: AudioBufferSourceNode.playbackRate
properties.description: Is an a-rate AudioParam that defines the speed factor at which the audio asset will be played. it default value is 1.0. When set to another value, the AudioBufferSourceNode applies pitch correction to the modified audio before to send it to the output. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: AudioBufferSourceNode.loop
properties.description: Is a Boolean attribute indicating if the play of the asset must restart when the end of the AudioBuffer is reached. Its default value is false.

properties.name: AudioBufferSourceNode.loopStart
properties.description: Is a double value indicating, in seconds, where in the AudioBuffer the restart of the play must happen. Its default value is 0.

properties.name: AudioBufferSourceNode.loopEnd
properties.description: Is a double value indicating, in seconds, where in the AudioBuffer the replay of the play must stop (and eventually loop again). Its default value is 0.

name: AudioContext
description: The AudioContext interface represents an audio-processing graph built from audio modules linked together, each represented by an AudioNode

properties.name: AudioContext.destination
properties.description: Returns an AudioDestinationNode representing the final destination of all audio in the context. It often represents an actual audio-rendering device.

properties.name: AudioContext.sampleRate
properties.description: Returns a float representing the sample rate, in samples per second, used by all node in this context. This limitation means that sample-rate converters are not supported.

properties.name: AudioContext.currentTime
properties.description: Returns a double representing an ever-increasing hardware time using for scheduling. It starts at 0 and cannot be stopped, paused or reset.

properties.name: AudioContext.listener
properties.description: Returns the AudioListener used for 3D spatialization.

name: AudioListener
description: The AudioListener interface represents the position and orientation of the unique person listening to the audio scene. All PannerNode spatialize in relation of the AudioListener stored in the AudioContext.listener attribute.

properties.name: AudioListener.dopplerFactor
properties.description: Is a double value representing the amount of pitch shift to use when rendering a doppler effect. Its default value is 1.

properties.name: AudioListener.speedOfSound
properties.description: Is a double value representing the speed of sound, in meters per second. Its default value is 343.3 m/s and is used to calculate the doppler shift (but no propagation delay is automatically applied to a sound far from the listener).

name: AudioNode
description: The AudioNode interface represents an audio-processing module, like an audio source (e.g. an HTML <audio> or <video> element), an audio destination, or an intermediate processing module (e.g. a filter like BiquadFilterNode, or a volume control like GainNode).

properties.name: AudioNode.context
properties.description: Links to the associated AudioContext, that is the object representing the processing graph the node is participating in.

name: AudioParam
description: The AudioParam interface represents an audio-related parameter, like one of an AudioNode, it can be set to a specific value or a change in value can be scheduled to happen at a specific time and following a specific pattern.

properties.name: AudioParam.value
properties.description: Represents the parameter current floating-point value. Initially it is set to the value of AudioParam.defaultValue. Though it can be set, any modification happening while there are automation events scheduled — that is events scheduled using the methods of the AudioParam — is ignored, without raising any exception.

properties.name: AudioParam.defaultValue
properties.description: Represents the initial value of the attributes as defined by the specific AudioNode creating the AudioParam.

name: AudioProcessingEvent
description: The Web Audio API AudioProcessingEvent represents events that occur when an ScriptProcessorNode input buffer is ready to be processed.

name: BatteryManager
description: The BatteryManager interface provides ways to get information about the system's battery charge level.

properties.name: BatteryManager.charging
properties.description: A Boolean value indicating whether or not the battery is currently being charged.

properties.name: BatteryManager.chargingTime
properties.description: A number representing the remaining time in seconds until the battery is fully charged, or 0 if the battery is already fully charged.

properties.name: BatteryManager.dischargingTime
properties.description: A number representing the remaining time in seconds until the battery is completely discharged and the system will suspend.

properties.name: BatteryManager.level
properties.description: A number representing the system's battery charge level scaled to a value between 0.0 and 1.0.

name: BiquadFilterNode
description: The BiquadFilterNode interface represents a simple low-order filter. It is an AudioNode that can represents different kind of filters, tone controls device or graphics equalizers. A BiquadFilterNode always has exactly one input and one output.

properties.name: BiquadFilterNode.frequency
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam of a double representing a frequency in the different filtering algorithm. Expressed in Hertz, its default value is 350 and a nominal range  of 10 to the Nyquist frequency, that is half of the sample rate. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: BiquadFilterNode.Q
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam of a double representing a Q factor, or quality factor. It is a dimensionless value and its default value is 1 and a nominal range of 0.0001 to 1000. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: BiquadFilterNode.gain
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam of a double representing the gain used in the filter algorithm. Positive it is a real gain, negative it is an attenuation. It is expressed in dB, has a default value of 0 and a nominal range of -40 to 40. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: BiquadFilterNode.type
properties.description:
Is a string value defining the kind of filter the node is implemented:

The meaning of the different parameters depending of the type of the filter
type Description frequency Q gain
lowpass Standard second-order resonant lowpass filter with 12dB/octave rolloff. Frequencies below the cutoff pass through; frequencies above it are attenuated. The cutoff frequency Indicates how peaked the frequency is around the cutoff. The greater the value is, the greater is the peak Not used
highpass Standard second-order resonant highpass filter with 12dB/octave rolloff. Frequencies below the cutoff are attenuated; frequencies above it pass through. The cutoff frequency Indicates how peaked the frequency is around the cutoff. The greater the value is, the greater is the peak Not used
bandpass Standard second-order bandpass filter. Frequencies outside the given range of frequencies are attenuated; the frequencies inside it pass through. The center of the range of frequencies. Controls the width of the frequency band. The greater Q is, the larger is the frequency band. Not used
lowshelf Standard second-order lowshelf filer. Frequencies lower than the frequency get a boost, or an attenuation; frequencies over it are unchanged. The upper limit of the frequencies getting a boost, or an attenuation Not used The boost, in dB, to be applied; if negative, it will be an attenuation.
highshelf Standard second-order highshelf filer. Frequencies higher than the frequency get a boost, or an attenuation; frequencies lower than it are unchanged. The lower limit of the frequencies getting a boost, or an attenuation Not used The boost, in dB, to be applied; if negative, it will be an attenuation.
peaking Frequencies inside the range get a boost, or an attenuation; frequencies outside it are unchanges. The middle of the frequency range getting a boost, or an attenauation Controls the width of the frequency band. The greater Q is, the larger is the frequency band. The boost, in dB, to be applied; if negative, it will be an attenuation.
notch Standard notch filter, also called band-stop or band-rejection filter. It is the opposite of a bandpass filter: frequencies outside the give range of frequencies pass through; frequencies inside it are attenuated. The center of the range of frequencies. Controls the width of the frequency band. The greater Q is, the larger is the frequency band. Not used
allpass Standard second-order allpass filter. Let all frequencies through, but change the phase-relationship between the various frequencies. The frequency with the maximal group delay, that is the frequency where the center of the phase transition occurs. Controls how sharp is the transition at the medium frequency. The larger this parameter is, the sharper the transition it, and the larger the transition. Not used

name: Blob
description: A Blob object represents a file-like object of immutable, raw data. Blobs represent data that isn't necessarily in a JavaScript-native format. The File interface is based on Blob, inheriting blob functionality and expanding it to support files on the user's system.

properties.name: size
properties.description: The size, in bytes, of the data contained in the Blob object. Read only.

properties.name: type
properties.description: An ASCII-encoded string, in all lower case, indicating the MIME type of the data contained in the Blob. If the type is unknown, this string is empty. Read only.

name: BlobBuilder
description: The BlobBuilder interface provides an easy way to construct Blob objects. Just create a BlobBuilder and append chunks of data to it by calling the append() method. When you're done building your blob, call getBlob() to retrieve a Blob containing the data you sent into the blob builder.

name: CallEvent
description: The DOM CallEvent represents events related to telephone calls.

properties.name: CallEvent.call
properties.description: A TelephonyCall object representing the call from which the event originated.

name: CameraCapabilities
description: The CameraControl.capabilities property returns a CameraCapabilities object, which describes all the camera's capabilities.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.effects
properties.description: An Array of strings identifying the effects (such as normal, sepia, mono, etc.) that the camera supports.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.fileFormats
properties.description: An Array of strings identifying the file formats supported by the camera, such as jpeg, rgb565, etc.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.flashModes
properties.description: An Array of strings identifying each of the flash modes supported by the camera. Possible values are auto, off, on or torch.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.focusModes
properties.description: An Array of strings identifying each of the focus modes supported by the camera such as auto, fixed, macro, etc.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.maxExposureCompensation
properties.description: A number that defines the maximum supported exposure compensation value.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.maxFocusAreas
properties.description: A number that defines the maximum number of focus areas supported by the camera.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.maxMeteringAreas
properties.description: A number that defines the maximum number of metering areas supported by the camera.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.minExposureCompensation
properties.description: A number that defines the minimum supported exposure compensation value.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.pictureSizes
properties.description: An Array of objects containing the height and width properties supported for picture taking.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.previewSizes
properties.description: An Array of objects containing the height and width properties supported for the video preview stream.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.recorderProfiles
properties.description: An object with attributes for each of the supported recorder profiles.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.sceneModes
properties.description: An Array of strings identifying each of the scene modes supported by the camera such as auto, night, beach, etc.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.stepExposureCompensation
properties.description: A number that defines the exposure compensation minimum step-size.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.videoSizes
properties.description: An Array of objects containing the height and width properties supported for video recording.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.whiteBalanceModes
properties.description: An Array of strings identifiers for each white balance modes supported by the camera such as auto, fluorecent, etc.

properties.name: CameraCapabilities.zoomRatios
properties.description: An Array of numbers representing all the supported zoom ratios. If the camera has no zoom capabilities, the value is null.

name: CameraControl
description: When you use the CameraManager.getCamera() method to get a reference to a camera, you specify a callback function to be invoked on success. That function receives as a parameter a CameraControl object. You can use its methods and properties to manage and make use of the camera.

properties.name: CameraControl.capabilities
properties.description: A CameraCapabilities object indicating all the capabilities for the given camera.

properties.name: CameraControl.effect
properties.description: A string defining the effect to be used by the camera (none by default). Its value must be one of the values available in CameraCapabilities.effects.

properties.name: CameraControl.exposureCompensation
properties.description: A value used to compensate the camera exposure. This attribute is read-only; to change the exposure, you need to call the CameraControl.setExposureCompensation() method.

properties.name: CameraControl.flashMode
properties.description: A string that defines how the flash, if any, is to be used; this is auto by default if the device has a flash, none otherwise. When set, its value must be chosen from the list of options specified by  CameraCapabilities.flashModes.

properties.name: CameraControl.focalLength
properties.description: A number that express the camera's focal length in millimeters.

properties.name: CameraControl.focusAreas
properties.description: An Array of one or more objects that define where the camera will perform auto-focusing.

properties.name: CameraControl.focusDistanceFar
properties.description: This value is a distance in meter used with CameraControl.focusDistanceNear to defined the image's depth of field. The value for this property may be Infinity.

properties.name: CameraControl.focusDistanceNear
properties.description: This value is a distance in meter used with CameraControl.focusDistanceFar to defined the image's depth of field.

properties.name: CameraControl.focusDistanceOptimum
properties.description: This value is a distance in meter where the subject will appear sharpest.

properties.name: CameraControl.focusMode
properties.description: A string that defines which kind of focus mode the camera should use (auto or fixed by default). Its value must be chosen from CameraCapabilities.focusModes.

properties.name: CameraControl.meteringAreas
properties.description: An Array of one or more objects that define where the camera will perform auto-focusing.

properties.name: CameraControl.onShutter
properties.description: A handler for the camera's "shutter" event, to trigger a shutter sound and/or a visual shutter indicator.

properties.name: CameraControl.onClosed
properties.description: A handler called when a new CameraControl object in the same app takes over the camera.

properties.name: CameraControl.onRecorderStateChange
properties.description: A function to call when the recorder changes state, either because the recording process encountered an error, or because one of the recording limits (see CameraControl.startRecording()) was reached.

properties.name: CameraControl.sceneMode
properties.description: A string that defines which scene mode the camera is to use (auto by default). Its value must be chosen from CameraCapabilities.sceneModes.

properties.name: CameraControl.whiteBalanceMode
properties.description: A string that defines which white balance mode the camera is to use (auto by default). Its value must be chosen from CameraCapabilities.whiteBalanceModes.

properties.name: CameraControl.zoom
properties.description: A number that defines which kind of zoom factor mode the camera is to use (1 by default). Its value must be chosen from CameraCapabilities.zoomRatios.

name: CameraManager
description: Provides access to any cameras available on the device being used.

name: CanvasGradient
description: This is an opaque object representing a gradient and returned by CanvasRenderingContext2D's createLinearGradient or createRadialGradient methods.

name: CanvasPattern
description: This is an opaque object created by CanvasRenderingContext2D's createPattern method (whether based on a image, canvas, or video).

name: CanvasPixelArray
description: Returned by ImageData's data attribute.

name: CanvasRenderingContext2D
description: The 2D rendering context for the drawing surface of a <canvas> element. To get this object, call getContext() on a <canvas>, supplying "2d" as the argument:

properties.name: canvas
properties.description: Back-reference to the canvas element for which this context was created. Read only.

properties.name: fillStyle
properties.description: Color or style to use inside shapes. Default #000 (black).

properties.name: font
properties.description: Default value 10px sans-serif.

properties.name: globalAlpha
properties.description: Alpha value that is applied to shapes and images before they are composited onto the canvas. Default 1.0 (opaque).

properties.name: globalCompositeOperation
properties.description:
With globalAlpha applied this sets how shapes and images are drawn onto the existing bitmap. Possible values:
  • source-atop
  • source-in
  • source-out
  • source-over (default)
  • destination-atop
  • destination-in
  • destination-out
  • destination-over
  • lighter
  • darker
  • copy
  • xor

properties.name: lineCap
properties.description: Type of endings on the end of lines. Possible values: butt (default), round, square

properties.name: lineDashOffset
properties.description: Specifies where to start a dasharray on a line.

properties.name: lineJoin
properties.description: Defines the type of corners where two lines meet. Possible values: round, bevel, miter (default)

properties.name: lineWidth
properties.description: Width of lines. Default 1.0

properties.name: miterLimit
properties.description: Default 10.

properties.name: shadowBlur
properties.description: Specifies the blurring effect. Default 0

properties.name: shadowColor
properties.description: Color of the shadow. Default fully-transparent black.

properties.name: shadowOffsetX
properties.description: Horizontal distance the shadow will be offset. Default 0.

properties.name: shadowOffsetY
properties.description: Vertical distance the shadow will be offset. Default 0.

properties.name: strokeStyle
properties.description: Color or style to use for the lines around shapes. Default #000 (black).

properties.name: textAlign
properties.description: Possible values: start (default), end, left, right or center.

properties.name: textBaseLine
properties.description: Possible values: top, hanging, middle, alphabetic (default), ideographic, bottom

name: CaretPosition
description: The CaretPosition interface represents the caret postion, an indicator for the text insertion point. You can get a CaretPosition using the document.caretPositionFromPoint method.

name: CDATASection
description: A CDATA Section can be used within XML to include extended portions of unescaped text, such that the symbols < and & do not need escaping as they normally do within XML when used as text.

name: ChannelMergerNode
description: The ChannelMergerNode interface, often used in conjunction with its opposite, ChannelSplitterNode, reunites different mono input in a single outputs. Each input will be used to fill a channel of the output. This is useful for accessing each channels separately, e.g. for performing channel mixing where gain must be separately controlled on each channel.

name: ChannelSplitterNode
description: The ChannelSplitterNode interface, often used in conjunction with its opposite, ChannelMergerNode, separates the different channels in a set of mono outputs. This is useful for accessing each channels seperately, e.g. for performing channel mixing where gain must be separately controlled on each channel.

name: CharacterData
description: Text, Comment, and CDATASection all implement CharacterData, which in turn also implements Node. See Node for the remaining methods, properties, and constants.

name: ChromeWorker
description: If you're developing privileged code, and would like to create a worker that can use js-ctypes to perform calls to native code, you can do so by using ChromeWorker instead of the standard Worker object. It works exactly like a standard Worker, except that it has access to js-ctypes via a global ctypes object available in the global scope of the worker.

name: CloseEvent
description: A CloseEvent is sent to clients using WebSockets when the connection is closed. This is delivered to the listener indicated by the WebSocket object's onclose attribute.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The WebSocket connection close code provided by the server. See Close codes for possible values.

properties.name: reason
properties.description: A string indicating the reason the server closed the connection. This is specific to the particular server and sub-protocol.

properties.name: wasClean
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the connection was cleanly closed.

name: CompositionEvent
description: The DOM CompositionEvent represents events that occur due to the user indirectly entering text.

properties.name: data
properties.description:
For compositionstart events, this is the currently selected text that will be replaced by the string being composed. This value doesn't change even if content changes the selection range; rather, it indicates the string that was selected when composition started.

For compositionupdate, this is the string as it stands currently as editing is ongoing.

For compositionend events, this is the string as committed to the editor.

Read only.

properties.name: locale
properties.description: The locale of current input method (for example, the keyboard layout locale if the composition is associated with IME). Read only.

name: console
description: The console object provides access to the browser's debugging console. The specifics of how it works vary from browser to browser, but there is a de facto set of features that are typically provided.

name: CSSConditionRule
description: An object implementing the CSSConditionRule DOM interface represents a single condition CSS at-rule, which consists of a condition and a statement block. It is a child of CSSGroupingRule.

properties.name: conditionText
properties.description: Represents the text of the condition of the rule.

name: CSSGroupingRule
description: An object implementing the CSSGroupingRule DOM interface represents any CSS at-rule that contains other rules nested in it.

name: CSSKeyframeRule
description: The CSSKeyframeRule interface describes an object representing a set of style for a given keyframe. It corresponds to the contains of a single keyframe of a @keyframes at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 8 (CSSRule.KEYFRAME_RULE).

name: CSSKeyframesRule
description: The CSSKeyframesRule interface describes an object representing a complete set of keyframes for a CSS animation. It corresponds to the contains of a whole @keyframes at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 7 (CSSRule.KEYFRAMES_RULE).

name: CSSMediaRule
description: CSSMediaRule is an object representing a single CSS @media rule. It implements the CSSConditionRule interface, and therefore the CSSGroupingRule and the CSSRule interface with a type value of 4 (CSSRule.MEDIA_RULE).

properties.name: media
properties.description: Specifies a MediaList representing the intended destination medium for style information.

name: CSSNamespaceRule
description: The CSSNamespaceRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS @namespace at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface, with a type value of 10 (CSSRule.NAMESPACE_RULE).

name: CSSPageRule
description: CSSPageRule is an object representing a single CSS @page rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 6 (CSSRule.PAGE_RULE).

properties.name: selectorText
properties.description: Represents the text of the page selector associated with the at-rule.

properties.name: style
properties.description: Returns the declaration block associated with the at-rule.

name: CSSRule
description: An object implementing the CSSRule DOM interface represents a single CSS at-rule. References to a CSSRule-implementing object may be obtained by looking at a CSS style sheet's cssRules list.

name: CSSRuleList
description: A CSSRuleList is an array-like object containing an ordered collection of CSSRule objects.

name: CSSStyleDeclaration
description: A CSSStyleDeclaration is an interface to the declaration block returned by the style property of a cssRule in a stylesheet, when the rule is a CSSStyleRule.

name: CSSStyleRule
description: CSSStyleRule represents a single CSS style rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 1 (CSSRule.STYLE_RULE).

name: CSSStyleSheet
description: An object implementing the CSSStyleSheet interface represents a single CSS style sheet.

properties.name: cssRules
properties.description: Returns a CSSRuleList of the CSS rules in the style sheet.

properties.name: ownerRule
properties.description: If this style sheet is imported into the document using an @import rule, the ownerRule property will return that CSSImportRule, otherwise it returns null.

name: CSSSupportsRule
description: The CSSSupportsRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS @supports at-rule. It implements the CSSConditionRule interface, and therefore the CSSRule and CSSGroupingRule interfaces with a type value of 12 (CSSRule.SUPPORTS_RULE).

name: CustomEvent
description: The DOM CustomEvent are events initialized by an application for any purpose.

properties.name: detail
properties.description: The data passed when initializing the event.

name: DataTransfer
description: This object is available from the dataTransfer property of all drag events. It cannot be created separately.

properties.name: dropEffect
properties.description:
The actual effect that will be used, and should always be one of the possible values of effectAllowed.

For the dragenter and dragover events, the dropEffect will be initialized based on what action the user is requesting. How this is determined is platform specific, but typically the user can press modifier keys to adjust which action is desired. Within an event handler for the dragenter and dragover events, the dropEffect should be modified if the action the user is requesting is not the one that is desired.

For dragstart, drag, and dragleave events, the dropEffect is initialized to "none". Any value assigned to the dropEffect will be set, but the value isn't used for anything.

For the drop and dragend events, the dropEffect will be initialized to the action that was desired, which will be the value that the dropEffect had after the last dragenter or dragover event.

Possible values:

  • copy: A copy of the source item is made at the new location.
  • move: An item is moved to a new location.
  • link: A link is established to the source at the new location.
  • none: The item may not be dropped.

Assigning any other value has no effect and retains the old value.

properties.name: effectAllowed
properties.description:
Specifies the effects that are allowed for this drag. You may set this in the dragstart event to set the desired effects for the source, and within the dragenter and dragover events to set the desired effects for the target. The value is not used for other events.

Possible values:

  • copy: A copy of the source item may be made at the new location.
  • move: An item may be moved to a new location.
  • link: A link may be established to the source at the new location.
  • copyLink: A copy or link operation is permitted.
  • copyMove: A copy or move operation is permitted.
  • linkMove: A link or move operation is permitted.
  • all: All operations are permitted.
  • none: the item may not be dropped.
  • uninitialized: the default value when the effect has not been set, equivalent to all.

Assigning any other value has no effect and retains the old value.

properties.name: files
properties.description:
Introduced in Gecko 1.9.2

(Firefox 3.6 / Thunderbird 3.1 / Fennec 1.0)

Contains a list of all the local files available on the data transfer. If the drag operation doesn't involve dragging files, this property is an empty list. An invalid index access on the FileList specified by this property will return null.

properties.name: mozCursor
properties.description:
Holds a list of the format types of the data that is stored for the first item, in the same order the data was added. An empty list will be returned if no data was added.

Gecko 1.9.2 note

The string "Files" is included in this list if files are included in the drag.

(Firefox 3.5 / Thunderbird 3.0 / SeaMonkey 2.0)

mozCursor

The drag cursor's state. This is primarily used to control the cursor during tab drags.

Note: This method is currently only implemented on Windows.

properties.name: mozItemCount
properties.description:
The number of items being dragged.

Note: This property is Gecko-specific.

properties.name: mozSourceNode
properties.description:
Introduced in Gecko 2

(Firefox 4 / Thunderbird 3.3 / SeaMonkey 2.1)

The Node over which the mouse cursor was located when the button was pressed to initiate the drag operation. This value is null for external drags or if the caller can't access the node.

Note: This property is Gecko-specific.

properties.name: mozUserCancelled
properties.description:
This property applies only to the dragend event, and is true if the user canceled the drag operation by pressing escape. It will be false in all other cases, including if the drag failed for any other reason, for instance due to a drop over an invalid location. This property is not currently implemented on Linux.

Note: This property is Gecko-specific.

properties.name: types
properties.description:
Set the drag source. Usually you would not change this, but it will affect which node the drag and dragend events are fired at. The default target is the node that was dragged.

name: DelayNode
description: The DelayNode interface represents a delay-line. It is an AudioNode, that is an audio-processing module, that causes a delay between the arrival of an input data and its propagation to the output. A DelayNode always has exactly one input and one output, both with the same amount of channels.

properties.name: DelayNode.delayTime
properties.description: Is an a-rate AudioParam representing the amount of delay to apply. It is expressed in seconds and its minimal value is 0 and its maximal value is defined by the maxDelayTime argument of the AudioContext.createDelay() factory method that created it. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

name: DeviceAcceleration
description: A DeviceAcceleration object provides information about the amount of acceleration the device is experiencing along all three axes.

properties.name: DeviceAcceleration.x
properties.description: The amount of acceleration along the X axis. Read only.

properties.name: DeviceAcceleration.y
properties.description: The amount of acceleration along the Y axis. Read only.

properties.name: DeviceAcceleration.z
properties.description: The amount of acceleration along the Z axis. Read only.

name: DeviceLightEvent
description: The DeviceLightEvent provides web developers with information from photo sensors or similiar detectors about ambient light levels near the device. For example this may be useful to adjust the screen's brightness based on the current ambient light level in order to save energy or provide better readability.

properties.name: DeviceLightEvent.value
properties.description: The level of the ambient light in lux.

name: DeviceMotionEvent
description: Editorial review completed.

properties.name: DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration
properties.description: An object giving the acceleration of the device on the three axis X, Y and Z. Acceleration is expressed in m/s2.

properties.name: DeviceMotionEvent.accelerationIncludingGravity
properties.description: An object giving the acceleration of the device on the three axis X, Y and Z with the effect of gravity. Acceleration is expressed in m/s2.

properties.name: DeviceMotionEvent.rotationRate
properties.description: An object giving the rate of change of the device's orientation on the three orientation axis alpha, beta and gamma. Rotation rate is express in degrees per seconds.

properties.name: DeviceMotionEvent.interval
properties.description: A number representing the interval of time, in milliseconds, at which data are obtain from the device.

name: DeviceOrientationEvent
description: The DeviceOrientationEvent provides web developers with information from the physical orientation of the device running the web page.

properties.name: DeviceOrientationEvent.absolute
properties.description: A boolean that indicates whether or not the device is providing orientation data absolutely.

properties.name: DeviceOrientationEvent.alpha
properties.description: A number representing the motion of the device around the z axis, express in degrees with values ranging from 0 to 360

properties.name: DeviceOrientationEvent.beta
properties.description: A number representing the motion of the device around the x axis, express in degrees with values ranging from -180 to 180. This represents a front to back motion of the device.

properties.name: DeviceOrientationEvent.gamma
properties.description: A number representing the motion of the device around the y axis, express in degrees with values ranging from -90 to 90. This represents a left to right motion of the device.

name: DeviceProximityEvent
description: The DeviceProximityEvent provides information about the distance of a nearby physical object using the proximity sensor of a device.

properties.name: DeviceProximityEvent.max
properties.description: The maximum sensing distance the sensor is able to report, in centimeters.

properties.name: DeviceProximityEvent.min
properties.description: The minimum sensing distance the sensor is able to report, in centimeters. Ususally zero.

properties.name: DeviceProximityEvent.value
properties.description: The current device proximity, in centimeters.

name: DeviceRotationRate
description: A DeviceRotationRate object provides information about the rate at which the device is rotating around all three axes.

properties.name: DeviceRotationRate.alpha
properties.description: The amount of rotation around the Z axis, in degrees per second.

properties.name: DeviceRotationRate.beta
properties.description: The amount of rotation around the X axis, in degrees per second.

properties.name: DeviceRotationRate.gamma
properties.description: The amount of rotation around the Y axis, in degrees per second.

name: DeviceStorage
description: The DeviceStorage interface is used to access files on a specific storage area available on the device. A storage area is basically the same thing as a file system repository even if it hides the reality of the underlaying file system.

properties.name: DeviceStorage.storageName
properties.description: A string representing the name of the storage. It's the same as the one use with getDeviceStorage to get the  DeviceStorage object.

properties.name: DeviceStorage.default
properties.description: A boolean that indicates if this storage area is the one which will be used by default for storing new files (true) or not (false).

name: DeviceStorageChangeEvent
description: The DeviceStorageChangeEvent provides information about any change made to a file inside a given storage area. It extend the Event interface.

properties.name: DeviceStorageChangeEvent.path
properties.description: A string giving the full path of the file affected by the change.

properties.name: DeviceStorageChangeEvent.reason
properties.description: A string giving the reason of the change. Possible values are created, modified or deleted.

name: DirectoryEntry
description: The DirectoryEntry interface of the FileSystem API represents a directory in a file system. It includes methods for creating, reading, looking up, and recursively removing files in a directory.

name: DirectoryEntrySync
description: The DirectoryEntrySync interface of the File System API represents a directory in a file system. It includes methods for creating, reading, looking up, and recursively removing files in a directory.

name: DirectoryReader
description: The DirectoryReader interface of the File System API lets you read the entries in a directory.

name: DirectoryReaderSync
description: The DirectoryReaderSync interface of the File System API lets you read the entries in a directory.

name: Document
description: Each web page loaded in the browser has its own document object. This object serves as an entry point to the web page's content (the DOM tree, including elements such as <body> and <table>) and provides functionality global to the document (such as obtaining the page's URL and creating new elements in the document).

properties.name: document.activeElement
properties.description: Returns the currently focused element

properties.name: document.alinkColor
properties.description: Returns or sets the color of active links in the document body.

properties.name: document.anchors
properties.description: Returns a list of all of the anchors in the document.

properties.name: document.applets
properties.description: Returns an ordered list of the applets within a document.

properties.name: document.async
properties.description: Used with document.load to indicate an asynchronous request.

properties.name: Node.attributes
properties.description: Returns a collection of attributes of the given element

properties.name: Node.baseURI
properties.description: Returns the base URL for the document

properties.name: Node.baseURIObject
properties.description: (Mozilla add-ons only!) Returns an nsIURI object representing the base URI for the document.

properties.name: document.bgColor
properties.description: Gets/sets the background color of the current document.

properties.name: document.body
properties.description: Returns the BODY node of the current document.

properties.name: document.characterSet
properties.description: Returns the character set being used by the document.

properties.name: Node.childNodes
properties.description: returns a collection of child nodes of the given node

properties.name: document.compatMode
properties.description: Indicates whether the document is rendered in Quirks or Strict mode.

properties.name: document.contentType
properties.description: Returns the Content-Type from the MIME Header of the current document.

properties.name: document.cookie
properties.description: Returns a semicolon-separated list of the cookies for that document or sets a single cookie.

properties.name: document.currentScript
properties.description: Returns the <script> element that is currently executing.

properties.name: document.defaultView
properties.description: Returns a reference to the window object.

properties.name: document.designMode
properties.description: Gets/sets WYSYWIG editing capability of Midas. It can only be used for HTML documents.

properties.name: document.dir
properties.description: Gets/sets directionality (rtl/ltr) of the document

properties.name: document.doctype
properties.description: Returns the Document Type Definition (DTD) of the current document.

properties.name: document.documentElement
properties.description: Returns the Element that is a direct child of document. For HTML documents, this is normally the HTML element.

properties.name: document.documentURI
properties.description: Returns the document location.

properties.name: document.documentURIObject
properties.description: (Mozilla add-ons only!) Returns the nsIURI object representing the URI of the document. This property only has special meaning in privileged JavaScript code (with UniversalXPConnect privileges).

properties.name: document.domain
properties.description: Returns the domain of the current document.

properties.name: document.domConfig
properties.description: Should return a DOMConfiguration object

properties.name: document.embeds
properties.description: Returns a list of the embedded OBJECTS within the current document.

properties.name: document.fgColor
properties.description: Gets/sets the foreground color, or text color, of the current document.

properties.name: document.fileSize
properties.description: (IE-only!) Returns size in bytes of the document. See MSDN.

properties.name: Node.firstChild
properties.description: Returns the first node in the list of direct children of the document, typically (but not limited to) the DocumentType (same as document.doctype) or the root element (document.documentElement)

properties.name: document.forms
properties.description: Returns a list of the FORM elements within the current document.

properties.name: document.head
properties.description: Returns the HEAD node of the current document.

properties.name: document.height
properties.description: Gets/sets the height of the current document.

properties.name: document.images
properties.description: Returns a list of the images in the current document.

properties.name: document.implementation
properties.description: Returns the DOM implementation associated with the current document.

properties.name: document.inputEncoding
properties.description: Returns the encoding used when the document was parsed.

properties.name: Node.lastChild
properties.description: Returns the last child of a node

properties.name: document.lastModified
properties.description: Returns the date on which the document was last modified.

properties.name: document.lastStyleSheetSet
properties.description: Returns the name of the style sheet set that was last enabled. Has the value null until the style sheet is changed by setting the value of selectedStyleSheetSet.

properties.name: document.linkColor
properties.description: Gets/sets the color of hyperlinks in the document.

properties.name: document.links
properties.description: Returns a list of all the hyperlinks in the document.

properties.name: Node.localName
properties.description: Returns the local part of the qualified name of this node (null for a document)

properties.name: document.location
properties.description: Returns the URI of the current document.

properties.name: document.mozSyntheticDocument
properties.description: true if this document is synthetic, such as a standalone image, video, audio file, or the like.

properties.name: document.mozFullScreen
properties.description: true when the document is in full-screen mode.

properties.name: document.mozFullScreenElement
properties.description: The element that's currently in full screen mode for this document.

properties.name: document.mozFullScreenEnabled
properties.description: true if calling element.mozRequestFullscreen() would succeed in the curent document.

properties.name: Node.namespaceURI
properties.description: Returns the XML namespace of the current document.

properties.name: Node.nextSibling
properties.description: Returns the node immediately following the specified one in its parent's childNodes list, or null if the specified node is the last node in that list (null for documents)

properties.name: Node.nodeName
properties.description: Returns the node's name (#document for document)

properties.name: Node.nodeType
properties.description: Returns a node type constant (9 for document)

properties.name: Node.nodeValue
properties.description: Returns the node's value (null for document)

properties.name: Node.nodePrincipal
properties.description: (Mozilla add-ons only!) Returns the nsIPrincipal object representing current security context of the document.

properties.name: Node.ownerDocument
properties.description: Returns the top-level document object for this node (null if already is the document).

properties.name: Node.parentNode
properties.description: Returns the parent of the specified node in the DOM tree (null for document)

properties.name: document.plugins
properties.description: Returns a list of the available plugins.

properties.name: document.popupNode
properties.description: Returns the node upon which a popup was invoked (XUL documents only).

properties.name: document.preferredStyleSheetSet
properties.description: Returns the preferred style sheet set as specified by the page author.

properties.name: Node.prefix
properties.description: Returns the namespace prefix of the specified node, or null if no prefix is specified

properties.name: Node.previousSibling
properties.description: Returns the node immediately preceding the specified one in its parent's childNodes list, null if the specified node is the first in that list (null for document)

properties.name: document.readyState
properties.description: Returns loading status of the document

properties.name: document.referrer
properties.description: Returns the URI of the page that linked to this page.

properties.name: document.scripts
properties.description: Returns all the <script> elements on the document.

properties.name: document.selectedStyleSheetSet
properties.description: Returns which style sheet set is currently in use.

properties.name: document.styleSheets
properties.description: Returns a list of the stylesheet objects on the current document.

properties.name: document.styleSheetSets
properties.description: Returns a list of the style sheet sets available on the document.

properties.name: Node.textContent
properties.description: Returns null (returns other values for other nodes).

properties.name: document.title
properties.description: Returns the title of the current document.

properties.name: document.tooltipNode
properties.description: Returns the node which is the target of the current tooltip.

properties.name: document.URL
properties.description: Returns a string containing the URL of the current document.

properties.name: document.vlinkColor
properties.description: Gets/sets the color of visited hyperlinks.

properties.name: document.width
properties.description: Returns the width of the current document.

properties.name: document.xmlEncoding
properties.description:
Returns the encoding as determined by the XML declaration.
Firefox 10 and later don't implement it anymore.

properties.name: document.xmlStandalone
properties.description: Returns true if the XML declaration specifies the document is standalone (e.g., An external part of the DTD affects the document's content), else false.

properties.name: document.xmlVersion
properties.description: Returns the version number as specified in the XML declaration or "1.0" if the declaration is absent.

name: DocumentFragment
description: DocumentFragment has no properties or methods of its own, but inherits from Node.

name: DocumentTouch
description: The DocumentTouch interface provides convenience methods for creating Touch and TouchList objects.

name: DocumentType
description: NOTE: This interface is not fully supported in Mozilla at present, including for indicating internalSubset information which Gecko generally does otherwise support.

name: DOMConfiguration
description: Pre-defined parameters: "canonical-form", "cdata-sections", "check-character-normalization", "comments", "datatype-normalization", "element-content-whitespace", "entities", "error-handler", "infoset", "namespaces", "namespace-declarations", "normalize-characters","schema-location", "schema-type", "split-cdata-sections", "validate", "validate-if-schema", "well-formed"

name: DOMCursor
description: A DOMCursor object represent an ongoing operation over a list of results. It is an enhanced DOMRequest that allows to iterate through a list of results asynchronously. Each time its continue() method is called, the DOMCursor tries to reach the next result in the list and calls its result's success or error accordingly.

properties.name: DOMCursor.done
properties.description: A boolean indicating if the cursor has reach the last result.

name: DOMError
description: This interface describes an error object that contains an error name.

name: DOMErrorHandler
description: NOTE: This is not implemented in Mozilla. For DOMException, see DOMException.

name: DOMImplementation
description: Provides methods which are not dependent on any particular DOM instances. Returned by document.implementation.

name: DOMImplementationList
description: Returned by DOMImplementationSource.getDOMImplementationList() and DOMImplementationRegistry.getDOMImplementationList() . Can be iterated with 0-based index.

name: DOMImplementationSource
description: Can request a particular implementation based on needed features and versions (which can then be used to create a document, etc.). Called during DOMImplementationRegistry.getDOMImplementation and DOMImplementationRegistry.getDOMImplementationList.

name: DOMLocator
description: NOTE: This is not implemented in Mozilla

name: DOMObject
description: For JavaScript, maps directly to a JavaScript object.

name: DOMParser
description: DOMParser can parse XML or HTML source stored in a string into a DOM Document. DOMParser is specified in DOM Parsing and Serialization.

name: DOMRequest
description: A DOMRequest object represents an ongoing operation. It provides callbacks that are called when the operation completes, as well as a reference to the operation's result. A DOM method that initiates an ongoing operation may return a DOMRequest object that you can use to monitor the progress of that operation.

properties.name: DOMRequest.onsuccess
properties.description: A callback handler called when the operation represented by the DOMRequest is completed.

properties.name: DOMRequest.onerror
properties.description: A callback handler that gets called when an error occurs while processing the operation.

properties.name: DOMRequest.readyState
properties.description: A string indicating whether or not the operation is finished running. Its value is either "done" or "pending".

properties.name: DOMRequest.result
properties.description: The operation's result.

properties.name: DOMRequest.error
properties.description: Error information, if any.

name: DOMString
description: A UTF-16 String. As JavaScript already uses such strings, DOMString is mapped directly to a String.

name: DOMStringList
description: A type returned by DOMConfiguration.parameterNames which contains a list of DOMString (strings).

name: DOMStringMap
description: Used by the dataset HTML attribute to represent data for custom attributes added to elements.

name: DOMTimeStamp
description: The DOMTimeStamp type represents an absolute or relative amount of milliseconds. It is bound to the Date object in JavaScript.  possesses this type.

name: DOMTokenList
description: This type represents a set of space-separated tokens. Commonly returned by HTMLElement.classList, HTMLLinkElement.relList, HTMLAnchorElement.relList or HTMLAreaElement.relList. It is indexed beginning with 0 as with JavaScript arrays. DOMTokenList is always case-sensitive.

name: DOMUserData
description: DOMUserData refers to application data. In JavaScript, it maps directly to Object. It is returned or used as an argument by Node.setUserData(), Node.getUserData(), used as the third argument to handle() on UserDataHandler, and is used or returned by various DOMConfiguration methods.

name: DynamicsCompressorNode
description: The DynamicsCompressorNode interface provides a dynamics compression effect, which lowers the volume of the loudest parts of the signal in order to help prevent clipping and distortion that can occur when multiple sounds are played and multiplexed together at once.

properties.name: DynamicsCompressorNode.threshold
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam representing the decibel value above which the compression start taking effect. Its default value is -24 and it can be set between -100 and 0. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: DynamicsCompressorNode.knee
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam containing a decibel value representing the range above the threshold where the curve smoothly transitions to the compressed portion. Its default value is 30 and it can be set between 0 and 40. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: DynamicsCompressorNode.ratio
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam representing the amount of change, in dB, needed in the input for a 1 dB change in the output. Its default value is 12 and it can be set between 1 and 20. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: DynamicsCompressorNode.reduction
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam representing the amount of gain reduction currently applied by the compressor to the signal. Intended for metering purpose, it returns a value in dB, or 0 (no gain reduction) if no signal is fed. The range of this value is between -20 and 0 (in dB). (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: DynamicsCompressorNode.attack
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam representing the amount of time, in seconds, to reduce the gain by 10 dB. It defines how quick the signal is adapted when its volume is increased. Its default value is 0.003 and it can be set between 0 and 1. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

properties.name: DynamicsCompressorNode.release
properties.description: Is a k-rate AudioParam representing the amount of time, in seconds, to increase the gain by 10 dB. It defines how quick the signal is adapted when its volume is reduced. Its default value is 0.25 and it can be set between 0 and 1. (Though the AudioParam returned is read-only, the value it represents is not.)

name: Element

properties.name: baseURIbaseURI
properties.description: Base URI as a string

properties.name: isContentEditable

properties.name: langlang
properties.description: Gets/sets the language of an element's attributes, text, and element contents.

properties.name: lastChildlastChild
properties.description: The last direct child node of an element, or null if this element has no child nodes.

properties.name: lastElementChild

properties.name: localNamelocalName
properties.description: The local part of the qualified name of an element. In Firefox 3.5 and earlier, the property upper-cases the local name for HTML elements (but not XHTML elements). name: Entry
description: The Entry interface of the FileSystem API represents an entry in a file system. The entry can be a file or a directory. It includes methods for working with files—including copying, moving, removing, and reading files—as well as information about file it points to—including the file name and its path from the root to the entry.

name: FileEntry

name: FileEntrySync

name: FileError
description: Represents an error that occurs while using the FileReader interface.

name: FileException
description: In the File System API, a FileException object represents error conditions that you might encounter while accessing the file system using the synchronous API. It extends the FileException interface described in File Writer and adds several new error codes.

name: FileList
description: An object of this type is returned by the files property of the HTML input element; this lets you access the list of files selected with the <input type="file"> element. It's also used for a list of files dropped into web content when using the drag and drop API; see the DataTransfer object for details on this usage.

name: FileReader
description: The FileReader object lets web applications asynchronously read the contents of files (or raw data buffers) stored on the user's computer, using File or Blob objects to specify the file or data to read. File objects may be obtained from a FileList object returned as a result of a user selecting files using the <input> element, from a drag and drop operation's DataTransfer object, or from the mozGetAsFile() API on an HTMLCanvasElement.

properties.description: The height of the rule.

properties.name: width
properties.description: The width of the rule on the page.

name: HTMLHtmlElement
description: The HTMLHtmlElement interface serves as the root node for a given HTML document.  This object inherits the properties and methods described in the HTMLElement interface.

properties.name: version
properties.description: Version of the HTML Document Type Definition (DTD) that governs this document. This property should not be used any more as it is non-conforming. Simply omit it.

name: HTMLIFrameElement
description: The HTMLIFrameElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of inline frame elements.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Specifies the alignment of the frame with respect to the surrounding context.

properties.name: allowfullscreen
properties.description: Indicates whether or not the inline frame is willing to be placed into full screen mode. See Using full-screen mode for details.

properties.name: contentDocument
properties.description: The active document in the inline frame's nested browsing context.

properties.name: contentWindow
properties.description: The window proxy for the nested browsing context.

properties.name: frameborder
properties.description: Indicates whether to create borders between frames.

properties.name: height
properties.description: Reflects the height HTML attribute, indicating the height of the frame.

properties.name: longDesc
properties.description: URI of a long description of the frame.

properties.name: marginHeight
properties.description: Height of the frame margin.

properties.name: marginWidth
properties.description: Width of the frame margin.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects the name HTML attribute, containing a name by which to refer to the frame.

properties.name: sandbox
properties.description: Reflects the sandbox HTML attribute, indicating extra restrictions on the behavior of the nested content.

properties.name: scrolling
properties.description: Indicates whether the browser should provide scrollbars for the frame.

properties.name: seamless
properties.description: Reflects the seamless HTML attribute, indicating that the inline frame should be rendered seamlessly within the parent document.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Reflects the src HTML attribute, containing the address of the content to be embedded.

properties.name: srcDoc
properties.description: The content to display in the frame.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Reflects the width HTML attribute, indicating the width of the frame.

name: HTMLImageElement
description: The HTMLImageElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of elements.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Indicates the alignment of the image with respect to the surrounding context.

properties.name: alt
properties.description: Reflects the alt HTML attribute, indicating fallback context for the image.

properties.name: border
properties.description: Width of the border around the image.

properties.name: complete
properties.description: True if the browser has fetched the image, and it is in a supported image type that was decoded without errors.

properties.name: crossOrigin
properties.description: The CORS setting for this image element. See CORS settings attributes for details.

properties.name: height
properties.description: Reflects the height HTML attribute, indicating the rendered height of the image in CSS pixels.

properties.name: hspace
properties.description: Space to the left and right of the image.

properties.name: isMap
properties.description: Reflects the ismap HTML attribute, indicating that the image is part of a server-side image map.

properties.name: longDesc
properties.description: URI of a long description of the image.

properties.name: lowSrc
properties.description: A reference to a low-quality (but faster to load) copy of the image.

properties.name: naturalHeight
properties.description: Intrinsic height of the image in CSS pixels, if it is available; otherwise, 0.

properties.name: naturalWidth
properties.description: Intrinsic width of the image in CSS pixels, if it is available; otherwise, 0.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Reflects the src HTML attribute, containing the URL of the image.

properties.name: useMap
properties.description: Reflects the usemap HTML attribute, containing a partial URL of a map element.

properties.name: vspace
properties.description: Space above and below the image.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Reflects the width HTML attribute, indicating the rendered width of the image in CSS pixels.

properties.name: x
properties.description: The horizontal offset from the nearest layer. (Mimic an old Netscape 4 behavior)

properties.name: y
properties.description: The vertical offset from the nearest layer. (Mimic an old Netscape 4 behavior)

name: HTMLInputElement
description: The HTMLInputElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of input elements.

properties.name: accept
properties.description: Reflects the accept HTML attribute, containing comma-separated list of file types accepted by the server when type is file.

properties.name: accessKey
properties.description: A single character that switches input focus to the control.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Alignment of the element.

properties.name: alt
properties.description: Reflects the alt HTML attribute, containing alternative text to use when type is image.

properties.name: autocomplete
properties.description:
Reflects the autocomplete HTML attribute, indicating whether the value of the control can be automatically completed by the browser. Ignored if the value of the type attribute is hidden, checkbox, radio, file, or a button type (button, submit, reset, image). Possible values are:
  • off: The user must explicitly enter a value into this field for every use, or the document provides its own auto-completion method; the browser does not automatically complete the entry.
  • on: The browser can automatically complete the value based on values that the user has entered during previous uses.

properties.name: autofocus
properties.description: Reflects the autofocus HTML attribute, which specifies that a form control should have input focus when the page loads, unless the user overrides it, for example by typing in a different control. Only one form element in a document can have the autofocus attribute. It cannot be applied if the type attribute is set to hidden (that is, you cannot automatically set focus to a hidden control).

properties.name: checked
properties.description: The current state of the element when type is checkbox or radio.

properties.name: defaultChecked
properties.description: The default state of a radio button or checkbox as originally specified in HTML that created this object.

properties.name: defaultValue
properties.description: The default value as originally specified in HTML that created this object.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Reflects the disabled HTML attribute, indicating that the control is not available for interaction. The input values will not be submitted with the form. See also readOnly

properties.name: files
properties.description: A list of selected files.

properties.name: form
properties.description:
The containing form element, if this element is in a form. If this element is not contained in a form element:
  • HTML5 this can be the id attribute of any <form> element in the same document. Even if the attribute is set on <input>, this property will be null, if it isn't the id of a <form> element.
  • HTML 4 this must be null.

properties.name: formAction
properties.description: Reflects the formaction HTML attribute, containing the URI of a program that processes information submitted by the element. If specified, this attribute overrides the action attribute of the <form> element that owns this element.

properties.name: formEncType
properties.description: Reflects the formenctype HTML attribute, containing the type of content that is used to submit the form to the server. If specified, this attribute overrides the enctype attribute of the <form> element that owns this element.

properties.name: formMethod
properties.description: Reflects the formmethod HTML attribute, containing the HTTP method that the browser uses to submit the form. If specified, this attribute overrides the method attribute of the <form> element that owns this element.

properties.name: formNoValidate
properties.description: Reflects the formnovalidate HTML attribute, indicating that the form is not to be validated when it is submitted. If specified, this attribute overrides the novalidate attribute of the <form> element that owns this element.

properties.name: formTarget
properties.description: Reflects the formtarget HTML attribute, containing a name or keyword indicating where to display the response that is received after submitting the form. If specified, this attribute overrides the target attribute of the <form> element that owns this element.

properties.name: height
properties.description: Reflects the height HTML attribute, which defines the height of the image displayed for the button, if the value of type is image.

properties.name: indeterminate
properties.description: Indicates that a checkbox is neither on nor off.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of <label> elements that are labels for this element.

properties.name: list
properties.description: Identifies a list of pre-defined options to suggest to the user. The value must be the id of a <datalist> element in the same document. The browser displays only options that are valid values for this input element. This attribute is ignored when the type attribute's value is hidden, checkbox, radio, file, or a button type.

properties.name: max
properties.description: Reflects the max HTML attribute, containing the maximum (numeric or date-time) value for this item, which must not be less than its minimum (min attribute) value.

properties.name: maxLength
properties.description:
Reflects the maxlength HTML attribute, containing the maximum length of text (in Unicode code points) that the value can be changed to. The constraint is evaluated only when the value is changed
Note: If you set maxLength to a negative value programmatically, an exception will be thrown.

properties.name: min
properties.description: Reflects the min HTML attribute, containing the minimum (numeric or date-time) value for this item, which must not be greater than its maximum (max attribute) value.

properties.name: multiple
properties.description: Reflects the multiple HTML attribute, indicating whether more than one value is possible (e.g., multiple files).

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects the name HTML attribute, containing a name that identifies the element when submitting the form.

properties.name: pattern
properties.description: Reflects the pattern HTML attribute, containing a regular expression that the control's value is checked against. The pattern must match the entire value, not just some subset. Use the title attribute to describe the pattern to help the user. This attribute applies when the value of the type attribute is text, search, tel, url or email; otherwise it is ignored.

properties.name: placeholder
properties.description: Reflects the placeholder HTML attribute, containing a hint to the user of what can be entered in the control. The placeholder text must not contain carriage returns or line-feeds. This attribute applies when the value of the type attribute is text, search, tel, url or email; otherwise it is ignored.

properties.name: readOnly
properties.description:
Reflects the readonly HTML attribute, indicating that the user cannot modify the value of the control.
HTML5This is ignored if the value of the type attribute is hidden, range, color, checkbox, radio, file, or a button type.

properties.name: required
properties.description: Reflects the required HTML attribute, indicating that the user must fill in a value before submitting a form.

properties.name: selectionDirection
properties.description: The direction in which selection occurred. This is "forward" if selection was performed in the start-to-end direction of the current locale, or "backward" for the opposite direction. This can also be "none" if the direction is unknown."

properties.name: selectionEnd
properties.description: The index of the end of selected text.

properties.name: selectionStart
properties.description: The index of the beginning of selected text.

properties.name: size
properties.description: Reflects the size HTML attribute, containing size of the control. This value is in pixels unless the value of type is text or password, in which case, it is an integer number of characters. HTML5 Applies only when type is set to text, search, tel, url, email, or password; otherwise it is ignored.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Reflects the src HTML attribute, which specifies a URI for the location of an image to display on the graphical submit button, if the value of type is image; otherwise it is ignored.

properties.name: step
properties.description: Reflects the step HTML attribute, which works with min and max to limit the increments at which a numeric or date-time value can be set. It can be the string any or a positive floating point number. If this is not set to any, the control accepts only values at multiples of the step value greater than the minimum.

properties.name: tabIndex
properties.description: The position of the element in the tabbing navigation order for the current document.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Reflects the type HTML attribute, indicating the type of control to display. See type attribute of <input> for possible values.

properties.name: useMap
properties.description: A client-side image map.

properties.name: validationMessage
properties.description: A localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.

properties.name: validity
properties.description: The validity state that this element is in.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Current value in the control.

properties.name: valueAsDate
properties.description: The value of the element, interpreted as a date, or null if conversion is not possible.

properties.name: valueAsNumber
properties.description:
The value of the element, interpreted as one of the following in order:
  1. a time value
  2. a number
  3. null if conversion is not possible

properties.name: width
