properties.description: Reflects the width HTML attribute, which defines the width of the image displayed for the button, if the value of type is image.

properties.name: willValidate
properties.description: Indicates whether the element is a candidate for constraint validation. It is false if any conditions bar it from constraint validation.

name: HTMLIsIndexElement
description: The HTMLIsIndexElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating <isindex> elements.

properties.name: HTMLBaseFontElement.form
properties.description: Is a HTMLFormElement representing the <form> element it belongs too. It can have the null value, if <isindex> isn't part of any form.

properties.name: HTMLBaseFontElement.prompt
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing a text to be prompted for the field.

name: HTMLKeygenElement
description: DOM keygen elements expose the HTMLKeygenElement interface, which provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular element object interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of keygen elements.

properties.name: autofocus
properties.description: Reflects the autofocus HTML attribute, indicating that the form control should have input focus when the page loads.

properties.name: challenge
properties.description: Reflects the challenge HTML attribute, containing a challenge string that is packaged with the submitted key.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Reflects the disabled HTML attribute, indicating that the control is not available for interaction.

properties.name: form
properties.description: Indicates the control's form owner, reflecting the form HTML attribute if it is defined.

properties.name: keytype
properties.description: Reflects the keytype HTML attribute, containing the type of key used.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of label elements associated with this keygen element.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects the name HTML attribute, containing the name for the control that is submitted with form data.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Must be the value keygen.

properties.name: validationMessage
properties.description: A localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.

properties.name: validity
properties.description: The validity states that this element is in.

properties.name: willValidate
properties.description: Always false because keygen objects are never candidates for constraint validation.

name: HTMLLabelElement
description: Editorial review completed.

properties.name: accessKey
properties.description: Reflects the accesskey HTML attribute.

properties.name: control
properties.description: The labeled control.

properties.name: form
properties.description: The form owner of this label.

properties.name: htmlFor
properties.description: The ID of the labeled control. Reflects the for attribute.

name: HTMLLegendElement
description: The HTMLLegendElement is an interface allowing to access properties of the <legend> elements. It inherits properties and methods from the HTMLElement interface.

properties.name: form
properties.description: The form that this legend belongs to. If the legend has a fieldset element as its parent, then this attribute returns the same value as the form attribute on the parent fieldset element. Otherwise, it returns null.

properties.name: accessKey
properties.description: A single-character access key to give access to the element.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Alignment relative to the form set

name: HTMLLIElement
description: The HTMLLIElement interface expose specific properties and methods (beyond those defined by regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating list elements.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the bullets, "disc", "square" or "circle". As the standard way of defining the list type is via the CSS list-style-type property, use the CSSOM methods to set it via a script.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Indicates the ordinal position of the list element inside a given <ol>. It reflects the attribute of the HTML <li> element, and can be smaller than 0. If the <li> element is not a child of an <ol> element, the property has no meaning.

name: HTMLLinkElement
description: The HTMLLinkElement interface represents reference information for external resources and the relationship of those resources to a document and vice-versa. This object inherits all of the properties and methods of the HTMLElement interface.

properties.name: charset
properties.description: Gets or sets the character encoding for the target resource.

properties.name: crossOrigin
properties.description: A DOMString that corresponds to the CORS setting for this link element. See CORS settings attributes for details.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Gets or sets whether the link is disabled; currently only used with style sheet links.

properties.name: href
properties.description: Gets or sets the URI for the target resource.

properties.name: hreflang
properties.description: Gets or sets the language code for the linked resource.

properties.name: media
properties.description: Gets or sets a list of one or more media formats to which the resource applies.

properties.name: rel
properties.description: Gets or sets the forward relationship of the linked resource from the document to the resource.

properties.name: relList
properties.description: Is a DOMTokenList that reflects the rel HTML attribute, as a list of tokens.

properties.name: rev
properties.description: Gets or sets the reverse relationship of the linked resource from the resource to the document.

properties.name: sizes
properties.description: Is a DOMSettableTokenList that reflects the sizes HTML attribute, as a list of tokens.

properties.name: target
properties.description: Gets or sets the name of the target frame to which the resource applies.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Gets or sets the MIME type of the linked resource.

name: HTMLMapElement
description: The HTMLMapElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of map elements.

properties.name: HTMLMapElement.name
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing the <map> element for referencing it other context. If the id attribute is set, this must have the same value; and it cannot be null or empty.

properties.name: HTMLMapElement.areas
properties.description: Is a live HTMLCollection representing the <area> elements associated to this <map>.

properties.name: HTMLMapElement.images
properties.description: Is a live HTMLCollection representing the <img> and <object> elements associated to this <map>.

name: HTMLMediaElement
description: The HTMLMediaElement interface has special properties and methods (beyond the properties and methods available for all children of HTMLElement), that are common to all media-related objects.

properties.name: audioTracks
properties.description: Represents the list of AudioTrack objects contained in the element.

properties.name: autoplay
properties.description: Reflects the autoplay HTML attribute, indicating whether playback should automatically begin as soon as enough media is available to do so without interruption.

properties.name: buffered
properties.description: The ranges of the media source that the browser has buffered (if any) at the moment the buffered property is accessed. The returned TimeRanges object is normalized.

properties.name: controller
properties.description: Represents the media controller associated to the element, or null if none is linked to it.

properties.name: controls
properties.description: Reflects the controls HTML attribute, indicating whether user interface items for controlling the resource should be displayed.

properties.name: crossOrigin
properties.description: The CORS setting for this image element. See CORS settings attributes for details.

properties.name: currentSrc
properties.description: The absolute URL of the chosen media resource (if, for example, the server selects a media file based on the resolution of the user's display), or an empty string if the networkState is EMPTY.

properties.name: currentTime
properties.description: The current playback time, in seconds. Setting this value seeks the media to the new time.

properties.name: defaultMuted
properties.description: Reflects the muted HTML attribute, indicating whether the media element's audio output should be muted by default. This property has no dynamic effect, to mute and unmute the audio output, use the muted property.

properties.name: defaultPlaybackRate
properties.description: The default playback rate for the media. 1.0 is "normal speed," values lower than 1.0 make the media play slower than normal, higher values make it play faster. The value 0.0 is invalid and throws a NOT_SUPPORTED_ERR exception.

properties.name: duration
properties.description: The length of the media in seconds, or zero if no media data is available.  If the media data is available but the length is unknown, this value is NaN.  If the media is streamed and has no predefined length, the value is Inf.

properties.name: ended
properties.description: Indicates whether the media element has ended playback.

properties.name: error
properties.description: The MediaError object for the most recent error, or null if there has not been an error.

properties.name: initialTime
properties.description: The initial playback position in seconds.

properties.name: loop
properties.description: Reflects the loop HTML attribute, indicating whether the media element should start over when it reaches the end.

properties.name: mediaGroup
properties.description: Reflects the mediagroup HTML attribute, indicating the name of the group of elements it belongs to. A group of media elements shares a common controller.

properties.name: mozChannels
properties.description: The number of channels in the audio resource (e.g., 2 for stereo).

properties.name: mozFrameBufferLength
properties.description:
Indicates the number of samples that will be returned in the framebuffer of each MozAudioAvailable event. This number is a total for all channels, and by default is set to be the number of channels * 1024 (e.g., 2 channels * 1024 samples = 2048 total).
The mozFrameBufferLength property can be set to a new value, for lower latency, or larger amounts of data, etc. The size given must be a number between 512 and 16384. Using any other size results in an exception being thrown. The best time to set a new length is after the loadedmetadata event fires, when the audio info is known, but before the audio has started or MozAudioAvailable events have begun firing.

properties.name: mozSampleRate
properties.description: The number of samples per second that will be played, for example 44100.

properties.name: mozSrcObject
properties.description: Allows to set or get the Media Stream to be played or being played.

properties.name: muted
properties.description: true if the audio is muted, and false otherwise.

properties.name: networkState
properties.description:
The current state of fetching the media over the network.
Constant Value Description
NETWORK_EMPTY 0 There is no data yet.  The readyState is also HAVE_NOTHING.
NETWORK_IDLE 1  
NETWORK_LOADING 2 The media is loading.
NETWORK_NO_SOURCE[1] 3

properties.name: paused
properties.description: Indicates whether the media element is paused.

properties.name: playbackRate
properties.description:
The current rate at which the media is being played back. This is used to implement user controls for fast forward, slow motion, and so forth. The normal playback rate is multiplied by this value to obtain the current rate, so a value of 1.0 indicates normal speed.
If the playbackRate is negative, the media is played backwards.
The audio is muted when the media plays backwards or if the fast forward or slow motion is outside a useful range (E.g. Gecko mute the sound outside the range 0.25 and 5.0).
The pitch of the audio is corrected by default and is the same for every speed. Some navigators implement the non-standard preservespitch property to control this.

properties.name: played
properties.description: The ranges of the media source that the browser has played, if any.

properties.name: preload
properties.description: Reflects the preload HTML attribute, indicating what data should be preloaded, if any. Possible values are: none, metadata, auto. See preload attribute documentation for details.

properties.name: readyState
properties.description:
The readiness state of the media.
Constant Value Description
HAVE_NOTHING 0 No information is available about the media resource.
HAVE_METADATA 1 Enough of the media resource has been retrieved that the metadata attributes are initialized.  Seeking will no longer raise an exception.
HAVE_CURRENT_DATA 2 Data is available for the current playback position, but not enough to actually play more than one frame.
HAVE_FUTURE_DATA 3 Data for the current playback position as well as for at least a little bit of time into the future is available (in other words, at least two frames of video, for example).
HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA 4 Enough data is available—and the download rate is high enough—that the media can be played through to the end without interruption.

properties.name: seekable
properties.description: The time ranges that the user is able to seek to, if any.

properties.name: seeking
properties.description: Indicates whether the media is in the process of seeking to a new position.

properties.name: src
properties.description:
Reflects the src HTML attribute, containing the URL of a media resource to use.
Gecko implements a similar functionality is available for streams: mozSrcObject.

properties.name: textTracks
properties.description: Represents the list of TextTrack objects contained in the element.

properties.name: videoTracks
properties.description: Represents the list of VideoTrack objects contained in the element.

properties.name: volume
properties.description: The audio volume, from 0.0 (silent) to 1.0 (loudest).

name: HTMLMetaElement
description: The HTMLMetaElement interface contains descriptive metadata about a document. Itt inherits all of the properties and methods described in the HTMLElement interface.

properties.name: content
properties.description: Gets or sets the value of meta-data property.

properties.name: httpEquiv
properties.description: Gets or sets the name of an HTTP response header to define for a document.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Gets or sets the name of a meta-data property to define for a document.

properties.name: scheme
properties.description: Gets or sets the name of a scheme used to interpret the value of a meta-data property.

name: HTMLMeterElement
description: The HTML <meter> elements expose the HTMLMeterElement interface, which provides special properties and methods (beyond the HTMLElement object interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <meter> elements.

properties.name: high
properties.description: It returns the value of the high boundary, reflecting the high <meter> attribute.

properties.name: low
properties.description: It returns the value of the low boundary, reflecting the low <meter> attribute.

properties.name: max
properties.description: It return the maximum value, reflecting the max <meter> attribute.

properties.name: min
properties.description: It returns the minimum value, reflecting the min <meter> attribute.

properties.name: optimum
properties.description: It retruns the optimum value, reflecting the min <meter> attribute.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of <label> elements that are labels for this element.

name: HTMLModElement
description: The HTMLModElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular methods and properties available through the HTMLElement interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating modification elements, that is <del> and <ins>.

properties.name: cite
properties.description: Reflects the cite HTML attribute, containing a URI of a resource explaining the change.

properties.name: datetime
properties.description: Reflects the datetime HTML attribute, containing a date-and-time string representing a timestamp for the change.

name: HTMLObjectElement
description: The HTMLObjectElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those on the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <object> element, representing external resources.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Enumerated property indicating alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", "justify", and "center".

properties.name: archive
properties.description: Reflects the archive HTML attribute, containing a list of archives for resources for this object.

properties.name: border
properties.description: Reflects the border HTML attribute, specifying the width of a border around the object.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The name of an applet class file, containing either the applet's subclass, or the path to get to the class, including the class file itself.

properties.name: codeBase
properties.description: Reflects the codebase HTML attribute, specifying the base path to use to resolve relative URIs.

properties.name: codeType
properties.description: Reflects the codetype HTML attribute, specifying the content type of the data.

properties.name: contentDocument
properties.description: The active document of the object element's nested browsing context, if any; otherwise null.

properties.name: contentWindow
properties.description: The window proxy of the object element's nested browsing context, if any; otherwise null.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Reflects the data HTML attribute, specifying the address of a resource's data.

properties.name: declare
properties.description: Reflects the declare HTML attribute, indicating that this is a declaration, not an instantiation, of the object.

properties.name: form
properties.description: The object element's form owner, or null if there isn't one.

properties.name: height
properties.description: Reflects the height HTML attribute, specifying the displayed height of the resource in CSS pixels.

properties.name: hspace
properties.description: Horizontal space in pixels around the control.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects the name HTML attribute, specifying the name of the object (HTML 4, or of a browsing context (HTML5.

properties.name: standby
properties.description: Reflects the standby HTML attribute, specifying a message to display while the object loads.

properties.name: tabindex
properties.description: The position of the element in the tabbing navigation order for the current document.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Reflects the type HTML attribute, specifying the MIME type of the resource.

properties.name: typeMustMatch
properties.description: Reflects the typeMustMatch HTML attribute, indicating if the resource specified by data must only be played if it matches the type attribute.

properties.name: useMap
properties.description: Reflects the usemap HTML attribute, specifying a <map> element to use.

properties.name: validationMessage
properties.description: A localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.

properties.name: validity
properties.description: The validity states that this element is in.

properties.name: vspace
properties.description: Horizontal space in pixels around the control.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Reflects the width HTML attribute, specifying the displayed width of the resource in CSS pixels.

properties.name: willValidate
properties.description: Indicates whether the element is a candidate for constraint validation. Always false for HTMLObjectElement objects.

name: HTMLOListElement
description: The HTMLOListElement interface provides special properties (beyond those defined on the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating ordered list elements.

properties.name: reversed
properties.description: Is a Boolean value reflecting the reversed and defining if the numbering is descending, that is its value is true, or ascending (false).

properties.name: start
properties.description: Is a long value reflecting the start and defining the value of the first number of the first element of the list.

properties.name: type
properties.description:
Is a DOMString value reflecting the type and defining the kind of marker to be used to display. It can have the following values:
  • '1' meaning that decimal numbers are used: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, …
  • 'a' meaning that the lowercase latin alphabet is used:  a, b, c, d, e, …
  • 'A' meaning that the uppercase latin alphabet is used: A, B, C, D, E, …
  • 'i' meaning that the lowercase latin numerals are used: i, ii, iii, iv, v, …
  • 'I' meaning that the uppercase latin numerals are used: I, II, III, IV, V, …

properties.name: compact
properties.description: Is a Boolean indicating that spacing between list items should be reduced. This property reflects the compact attribute only, it doesn't consider the line-height CSS property used for that behavior in modern pages.

name: HTMLOptGroupElement
description: The HTMLOptGroupElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement object interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <optgroup> elements.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: If true, the whole list of children <option> is disabled

properties.name: label
properties.description: Set or get the label for the group.

name: HTMLOptionElement
description: The HTMLOptionElement interface represents <option> elements and inherits all classes and methods of the HTMLElement interface.

properties.name: defaultSelected
properties.description: Contains the initial value of the selected HTML attribute, indicating whether the option is selected by default or not.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Reflects the value of the disabled HTML attribute, which indicates that the option is unavailable to be selected. An option can also be disabled if it is a child of an <optgroup> element that is disabled.

properties.name: form
properties.description: If the option is a descendant of a <select> element, then this property has the same value as the form property of the corresponding HTMLSelectElement object; otherwise, it is null.

properties.name: index
properties.description: The position of the option within the list of options it belongs to, in tree-order. If the option is not part of a list of options, like when it is part of the <datalist> element, the value is 0.

properties.name: label
properties.description: Reflects the value of the label HTML attribute, which provides a label for the option. If this attribute isn't specifically set, reading it returns the element's text content.

properties.name: selected
properties.description: Indicates whether the option is currently selected.

properties.name: text
properties.description: Contains the text content of the element.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Reflects the value of the value HTML attribute, if it exists; otherwise reflects value of the Node.textContent property.

name: HTMLOptionsCollection
description: HTMLOptionsCollection is an interface representing a collection of HTML option elements (in document order) and offers methods and properties for traversing the list as well as optionally altering its items. This type is returned solely by the "options" property of select.

properties.name: length
properties.description: As optionally allowed by the spec, Mozilla allows this property to be set, either removing options at the end when using a shorter length, or adding blank options at the end when setting a longer length. Other implementations could potentially throw a DOMException.

name: HTMLOutputElement
description: The HTMLOutputElement interface provides properties and methods (beyond those inherited from HTMLElement) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <output> elements.

properties.name: defaultValue
properties.description: The default value of the element, initially the empty string.

properties.name: form
properties.description: Indicates the control's form owner, reflecting the form HTML attribute if it is defined.

properties.name: htmlFor
properties.description: Reflects the for HTML attribute, containing a list of IDs of other elements in the same document that contribute to (or otherwise affect) the calculated value.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of label elements associated with this output element.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects the name HTML attribute, containing the name for the control that is submitted with form data.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Must be the string output.

properties.name: validationMessage
properties.description: A localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.

properties.name: validity
properties.description: The validity states that this element is in.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The value of the contents of the elements. Behaves like the Node.textContent property.

properties.name: willValidate
properties.description:
The behavior of this property is subject to an open specification bug, as some browser maker are not happy with what is specified. It is unclear which will be the final the outcome of this.

The standard behavior is to always return false because output objects are never candidates for constraint validation.

The proposed new behavior, implemented in Firefox since Gecko 2.0 is to use this property to indicate whether the element is a candidate for constraint validation. It is false if any conditions bar it from constraint validation (See ).

name: HTMLParagraphElement
description:
The HTMLParagraphElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement object interface it inherits) for manipulating

elements.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Enumerated property indicating alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", "justify", and "center".

name: HTMLParamElement
description: The HTMLParamElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement object interface it inherits) for manipulating <param> elements, representing a pair of a key and a value that acts as a parameter for an <object> element.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing the name of the parameter. It reflects the name attribute.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing the value associated to the parameter. It reflects the value attribute.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the type of the parameter when valueType has the "ref" value. It reflects the type attribute.

properties.name: valueType
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the type of the value. It reflects the valuetype attribute and has one of the values: "data", "ref", or "object".

name: HTMLPreElement
description: The HTMLPreElement interface expose specific properties and methods (beyond those defined by regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating block of preformatted text.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Is a long value reflecting the obsolete width attribute, containing a fixed-size length for the <pre> element.

name: HTMLProgressElement
description: The HTMLProgressElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <progress> elements.

properties.name: max
properties.description: This property reflect the content attribute of the same name, limited to numbers greater than zero. Its default value is 1.0.

properties.name: position
properties.description: If the progress bar is an indeterminate progress bar, then the position property return −1. Otherwise, it returns the result of dividing the current value by the maximum value.

properties.name: value
properties.description: If the progress bar is an indeterminate progress bar, then this property return 0. Otherwise, it returns the current value.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of <label> elements that are labels for this element.

name: HTMLQuoteElement
description: The HTMLQuoteElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating quoting elements, like <blockquote> and <q>, but not the <cite> element.

properties.name: cite
properties.description: Reflects the cite HTML attribute, containing a URL for the source of the quotation.

name: HTMLScriptElement
description: DOM Script objects expose the HTMLScriptElement (or HTML 4 HTMLScriptElement) interface, which provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular element object interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <script> elements.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Represents the MIME type of the script. It reflects the type attribute.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Represents gives the address of the external script resource to use. It reflects the src attribute.

properties.name: htmlFor
properties.description: [Description missing]

properties.name: event
properties.description: [Description missing]

properties.name: charset
properties.description: Represents the character encoding of the external script resource. It reflects the charset attribute.

properties.name: async
properties.description:
The async and defer attributes are boolean attributes that indicate how the script should be executed. The defer and async attributes must not be specified if the src attribute is not present.

There are three possible modes that can be selected using these attributes. If the async attribute is present, then the script will be executed asynchronously, as soon as it is available. If the async attribute is not present but the defer attribute is present, then the script is executed when the page has finished parsing. If neither attribute is present, then the script is fetched and executed immediately, before the user agent continues parsing the page.

Note: The exact processing details for these attributes are, for mostly historical reasons, somewhat non-trivial, involving a number of aspects of HTML. The implementation requirements are therefore by necessity scattered throughout the specification. These algorithms describe the core of this processing, but these algorithms reference and are referenced by the parsing rules for <script> start and end tags in HTML, in foreign content, and in XML, the rules for the document.write() method, the handling of scripting, etc.

The defer attribute may be specified even if the async attribute is specified, to cause legacy Web browsers that only support defer (and not async) to fall back to the defer behavior instead of the synchronous blocking behavior that is the default.

properties.name: crossOrigin
properties.description: Is a DOMString that corresponds to the CORS setting for this script element. See CORS settings attributes for details. It controls, for scripts that are obtained from other origins, whether error information will be exposed.

properties.name: text
properties.description:
The IDL attribute text must return a concatenation of the contents of all the Text nodes that are children of the <script> element (ignoring any other nodes such as comments or elements), in tree order. On setting, it must act the same way as the textContent IDL attribute.

Note: When inserted using the document.write() method, <script> elements execute (typically synchronously), but when inserted using innerHTML and outerHTML attributes, they do not execute at all.

name: HTMLSelectElement
description: DOM select elements share all of the properties and methods of other HTML elements described in the element section. They also have the specialized interface HTMLSelectElement (or HTML 4 HTMLSelectElement).

properties.name: autofocus
properties.description: Reflects the autofocus HTML attribute, which indicates whether the control should have input focus when the page loads, unless the user overrides it, for example by typing in a different control. Only one form-associated element in a document can have this attribute specified. HTML5 Requires Gecko 2.0

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Reflects the disabled HTML attribute, which indicates whether the control is disabled. If it is disabled, it does not accept clicks.

properties.name: form
properties.description:
The form that this element is associated with. If this element is a descendant of a form element, then this attribute is the ID of that form element. If the element is not a descendant of a form element, then:
  • HTML5 The attribute can be the ID of any form element in the same document.
  • HTML 4 The attribute is null.
Read only.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of label elements associated with this select element.

properties.name: length
properties.description: The number of <option> elements in this select element.

properties.name: multiple
properties.description: Reflects the multiple HTML attribute, whichindicates whether multiple items can be selected.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects the name HTML attribute, containing the name of this control used by servers and DOM search functions.

properties.name: options
properties.description: The set of <option> elements contained by this element. Read only.

properties.name: required
properties.description: Reflects the required HTML attribute, which indicates whether the user is required to select a value before submitting the form. HTML5 Requires Gecko 2.0

properties.name: selectedIndex
properties.description: The index of the first selected <option> element.

properties.name: selectedOptions
properties.description: The set of options that are selected. HTML5

properties.name: size
properties.description: Reflects the size HTML attribute, which contains the number of visible items in the control. The default is 1, HTML5 unless multiple is true, in which case it is 4.

properties.name: tabIndex
properties.description: The element's position in the tabbing order. HTML 4 Obsolete since HTML5

properties.name: type
properties.description: The form control's type. When multiple is true, it returns select-multiple; otherwise, it returns select-one.Read only.

properties.name: validationMessage
properties.description: A localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This attribute is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.Read only. HTML5 Requires Gecko 2.0

properties.name: validity
properties.description: The validity states that this control is in. Read only. HTML5 Requires Gecko 2.0

properties.name: value
properties.description: The value of this form control, that is, of the first selected option.

properties.name: willValidate
properties.description: Indicates whether the button is a candidate for constraint validation. It is false if any conditions bar it from constraint validation. Read only. HTML5 Requires Gecko 2.0

name: HTMLSourceElement
description: The HTMLSourceElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating <source> elements.

properties.name: media
properties.description: Reflects the media HTML attribute, containing the intended type of the media resource.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Reflects the src HTML attribute, containing the URL for the media resource.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Reflects the type HTML attribute, containing the type of the media resource.

name: HTMLSpanElement
description: The HTMLSpanElement interface represents a <span> element and derives from the HTMLElement interface, but without implementing any additional properties or methods.

name: HTMLStyleElement
description: The HTMLStyleElement interface represents a <style> element. It inherits properties and methods from its parent, HTMLElement and from LinkStyle.

properties.name: HTMLStyleElement.media
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing the intended destination medium for style information.

properties.name: HTMLStyleElement.type
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing the type of style being applied by this statement.

properties.name: HTMLStyleElement.disabled
properties.description: Is a Boolean value, with true if the stylesheet is disabled, and false if not.

properties.name: HTMLStyleElement.scoped
properties.description: Is a Boolean value indicating if the element applies to the whole document (false) or only to the parent's sub-tree (true).

name: HTMLTableCaptionElement
description: The HTMLTableCaptionElement interface special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating table caption elements.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Enumerated attribute indicating alignment of the caption with respect to the table.

name: HTMLTableCellElement
description: The HTMLTableCellElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of table cells, either header or data cells, in an HTML document.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.colspan
properties.description: Is an unsigned long that represents the number of columns this cell must span. It reflects the attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.rowspan
properties.description: Is an unsigned long that represents the number of rows this cell must span. It reflects the attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.headers
properties.description: Is a DOMSettableTokenList describing a list of id of <th> elements that represents headers associated with the cell. It reflects the attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.cellIndex
properties.description: Is a long representing the cell position in the cells collection of the <tr> it belongs to. If the cell doesn't belong to a <tr>, it returns -1.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.align
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing an enumerated value reflecting the attribute. It indicates the alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", and "center".

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.bgColor
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the background color of the cells. It reflects the obsolete attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.axis
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a name grouping cells in virtual. It reflects the obsolete attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.height
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a length of pixel of the hinted height of the cell. It reflects the obsolete attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.width
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a length of pixel of the hinted width of the cell. It reflects the obsolete attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.ch
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing one single chararcter. This character is the one to align all the cell of a column on. It reflects the and default to the decimal points associated with the language, e.g. '.' for English, or ',' for French. This property was optional and was not very well supported.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.chOff
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a integer indicating how many characters must be left at the right (for left-to-right scripts; or at the left for right-to-left scripts) of the character defined by HTMLTableCellElement.ch. This property was optional and was not very well supported.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.noWrap
properties.description: Is a Boolean value reflecting the attribute and indicating if cell content can be broken in several lines.

properties.name: HTMLTableCellElement.vAlign
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing an enumerated value indicating how the content of the cell must be vertically aligned. It reflects the attribute and can have one of the following values: "top", "middle", "bottom", or "baseline".

name: HTMLTableColElement
description: The HTMLTableColElement interface provides special properties (beyond the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it inheritance) for manipulating single or grouped table column elements.

properties.name: align
properties.description: Indicates the horizontal alignment of the cell data in the column.

properties.name: ch
properties.description: Alignment character for cell data.

properties.name: chOff
properties.description: Offset for the alignment character.

properties.name: span
properties.description: Reflects the span HTML attribute, indicating the number of columns to apply this object's attributes to. Must be a positive integer.

properties.name: vAlign
properties.description: Indicates the vertical alignment of the cell data in the column.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Default column width.

name: HTMLTableElement
description: The HTMLTableElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of tables in an HTML document.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.caption
properties.description: Is an HTMLTableCaptionElement representing the first <caption> that is a child of the element, or null if none is found. When set, if the object doesn't represent a <caption>, a DOMException with the HierarchyRequestError name is thrown. If a correct object is given, it is inserted in the tree as the first child of this element and the first <caption> that is a child of this element is removed from the tree, if any.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.tHead
properties.description: Is an HTMLTableSectionElement representing the first <thead> that is a child of the element, or null if none is found. When set, if the object doesn't represent a <thead>, a DOMException with the HierarchyRequestError name is thrown. If a correct object is given, it is inserted in the tree immediately before the first element that is neither a <caption>, nor a <colgroup>, or as the last child if there is no such element, and the first <thead> that is a child of this element is removed from the tree, if any.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.tFoot
properties.description: Is an HTMLTableSectionElement representing the first <tfoot> that is a child of the element, or null if none is found. When set, if the object doesn't represent a <tfoot>, a DOMException with the HierarchyRequestError name is thrown. If a correct object is given, it is inserted in the tree immediately before the first element that is neither a <caption>, a <colgroup>, nor a <thead>, or as the last child if there is no such element, and the first <tfoot> that is a child of this element is removed from the tree, if any.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.rows
properties.description: Returns a live HTMLCollection containing all the rows of the element, that is all <tr> that are a child of the element, or a child or one of its <thead>, <tbody> and <tfoot> children. The rows members of a <thead> appear first, in tree order, and those members of a <tbody> last, also in tree order. The HTMLCollection is live and is automatically updated when the HTMLTableElement changes.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.tBodies
properties.description: Returns a live HTMLCollection containing all the <tbody> of the element. The HTMLCollection is live and is automatically updated when the HTMLTableElement changes.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.sortable
properties.description: Is a Boolean value indicating if the user agent is allowed to provide sorting mechanism for the table, if it supports such a feature. This property reflects the sortable attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.align
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing an enumerated value reflecting the align attribute. It indicates the alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", and "center".

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.bgColor
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the background color of the cells. It reflects the obsolete bgColor attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.border
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the width in pixels of the border of the table. It reflects the obsolete border attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.cellPadding
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the width in pixels of the horizontal and vertical sapce between cell content and cell borders. It reflects the obsolete cellpadding attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.cellSpacing
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the width in pixels of the horizontal and vertical separation between cells. It reflects the obsolete cellspacing attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.frame
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the type of the external borders of the table. It reflects the obsolete frame attribute and can take one of the following values: "void", "above", "below", "hsides", "vsides", "lhs", "rhs", "box", or "border".

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.rules
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the type of the internal borders of the table. It reflects the obsolete rules attribute and can take one of the following values: "none", "groups", "rows", "cols", or "all".

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.summary
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a description of the purpose or the structure of the table. It reflects the obsolete summary attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableElement.width
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the length in pixels or in percentage of the desired width fo the entire table. It reflects the obsolete width attribute.

name: HTMLTableRowElement
description: The HTMLTableRowElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of rows in an HTML table.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.align
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing an enumerated value reflecting the align attribute. It indicates the alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", and "center".

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.bgColor
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing the background color of the cells. It reflects the obsolete bgColor attribute.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.cells
properties.description: Returns a live HTMLCollection containing the cells in the row. The HTMLCollection is live and is automatically updated when cells are added or removed.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.ch
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing one single chararcter. This character is the one to align all the cell of a column on. It reflects the char and default to the decimal points associated with the language, e.g. '.' for English, or ',' for French. This property was optional and was not very well supported.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.chOff
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a integer indicating how many characters must be left at the right (for left-to-right scripts; or at the left for right-to-left scripts) of the character defined by HTMLTableRowElement.ch. This property was optional and was not very well supported.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.rowIndex
properties.description: Returns a long value which gives the logical position of the row within the entire table. If the row is not part of a table, returns -1.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.sectionRowIndex
properties.description: Returns a long value which gives the logical position of the row within the table section it belongs to. If the row is not part of a section, returns -1.

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.vAlign
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing an enumerated value indicating how the content of the cell must be vertically aligned. It reflects the valign attribute and can have one of the following values: "top", "middle", "bottom", or "baseline".

name: HTMLTableSectionElement
description: The HTMLTableSectionElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of sections, that is headers, footers and bodies, in an HTML table.

properties.name: HTMLTableSectionElement.align
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing an enumerated value reflecting the align attribute. It indicates the alignment of the element's contents with respect to the surrounding context. The possible values are "left", "right", and "center".

properties.name: HTMLTableRowElement.rows
properties.description: Returns a live HTMLCollection containing the rows in the section. The HTMLCollection is live and is automatically updated when rows are added or removed.

properties.name: HTMLTableSectionElement.ch
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing one single chararcter. This character is the one to align all the cell of a column on. It reflects the char and default to the decimal points associated with the language, e.g. '.' for English, or ',' for French. This property was optional and was not very well supported.

properties.name: HTMLTableSectionElement.chOff
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a integer indicating how many characters must be left at the right (for left-to-right scripts; or at the left for right-to-left scripts) of the character defined by HTMLTableRowElement.ch. This property was optional and was not very well supported.

properties.name: HTMLTableSectionElement.vAlign
properties.description: Is a DOMString representing an enumerated value indicating how the content of the cell must be vertically aligned. It reflects the valign attribute and can have one of the following values: "top", "middle", "bottom", or "baseline".

name: HTMLTextAreaElement
description: The HTMLTextAreaElement interface, which provides special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <textarea> elements.

properties.name: accessKey
properties.description: Reflects the accesskey HTML attribute.

properties.name: autofocus
properties.description: Reflects the autofocus HTML attribute, indicating that the control should have input focus when the page loads

properties.name: cols
properties.description: Reflects the cols HTML attribute, indicating the visible width of the text area.

properties.name: defaultValue
properties.description: The control's default value, which behaves like the element.textContent property.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Reflects the disabled HTML attribute, indicating that the control is not available for interaction.

properties.name: form
properties.description: The containing form element, if this element is in a form. If this element is not contained in a form element, it can be the id attribute of any <form> element in the same document or the value null.

properties.name: labels
properties.description: A list of <label> elements that are labels for this element.

properties.name: maxLength
properties.description: Reflects the maxlength HTML attribute, indicating the maximum number of characters the user can enter. This constraint is evaluated only when the value changes.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Reflects name HTML attribute, containing the name of the control.

properties.name: placeholder
properties.description: Reflects the placeholder HTML attribute, containing a hint to the user about what to enter in the control.

properties.name: readOnly
properties.description: Reflects the readonly HTML attribute, indicating that the user cannot modify the value of the control.

properties.name: required
properties.description: Reflects the required HTML attribute, indicating that the user must specify a value before submitting the form.

properties.name: rows
properties.description: Reflects the rows HTML attribute, indicating the number of visible text lines for the control.

properties.name: selectionDirection
properties.description: The direction in which selection occurred. This is "forward" if selection was performed in the start-to-end direction of the current locale, or "backward" for the opposite direction. This can also be "none" if the direction is unknown."

properties.name: selectionEnd
properties.description: The index of the end of selected text. If no text is selected, contains the index of the character that follows the input cursor. On being set, the control behaves as if setSelectionRange() had been called with this as the second argument, and selectionStart as the first argument.

properties.name: selectionStart
properties.description: The index of the beginning of selected text. If no text is selected, contains the index of the character that follows the input cursor. On being set, the control behaves as if setSelectionRange() had been called with this as the first argument, and selectionEnd as the second argument.

properties.name: tabIndex
properties.description: The position of the element in the tabbing navigation order for the current document.

properties.name: textLength
properties.description: The codepoint length of the control's value.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The string textarea.

properties.name: validationMessage
properties.description: A localized message that describes the validation constraints that the control does not satisfy (if any). This is the empty string if the control is not a candidate for constraint validation (willValidate is false), or it satisfies its constraints.

properties.name: validity
properties.description: The validity states that this element is in.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The raw value contained in the control.

properties.name: willValidate
properties.description: Indicates whether the element is a candidate for constraint validation. It is false if any conditions bar it from constraint validation.

properties.name: wrap
properties.description: Reflects the wrap HTML attribute, indicating how the control wraps text.

name: HTMLTimeElement
description: The HTMLTimeElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating <time> elements.

properties.name: dateTime
properties.description: Reflects the datetime HTML attribute, containing a machine-readable form of the element's date and time value.

name: HTMLTitleElement
description: The HTMLTitleElement interface contains the title for a document. This element inherits all of the properties and methods of the HTMLElement interface.

properties.name: HTMLTitleElement.text
properties.description: DOMString representing the text of the document's title.

name: HTMLTrackElement
description: The HTMLTrackElement interface provides access to the properties of <track> elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

properties.name: kind
properties.description: Reflects the kind HTML attribute, indicating how the text track is meant to be used. Possible values are: subtitles, captions, descriptions, chapters, metadata. See kind attribute documentation for details.

properties.name: src
properties.description: Reflects the src HTML attribute, indicating the address of the text track data.

properties.name: srclang
properties.description: Reflects the srclang HTML attribute, indicating the language of the text track data.

properties.name: label
properties.description: Reflects the label HTML attribute, indicating a user-readable title for the track.

properties.name: default
properties.description: Reflects the default HTML attribute, indicating that the track is to be enabled if the user's preferences do not indicate that another track would be more appropriate.

properties.name: readyState
properties.description:
The readiness state of the track.

Constant Value Description
NONE 0 Indicates that the text track's cues have not been obtained.
LOADING 1 Indicates that the text track is loading and there have been no fatal errors encountered so far. Further cues might still be added to the track by the parser.
LOADED 2 Indicates that the text track has been loaded with no fatal errors.
ERROR 3 Indicates that the text track was enabled, but when the user agent attempted to obtain it, this failed in some way. Some or all of the cues are likely missing and will not be obtained.

properties.name: track
properties.description: The track element's text track data.

name: HTMLUListElement
description: The HTMLUListElement interface provides special properties (beyond those defined on the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating unordered list elements.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Is a DOMString value reflecting the type and defining the kind of marker to be used to display. The values are browser dependent and have never been standardized.

properties.name: compact
properties.description: Is a Boolean indicating that spacing between list items should be reduced. This property reflects the compact attribute only, it doesn't consider the line-height CSS property used for that behavior in modern pages.

name: HTMLUnknownElement
description: The HTMLUnknownElement interface represents an invalid HTML element and derives from the HTMLElement interface, but without implementing any additional properties or methods.

name: HTMLVideoElement
description: The HTMLVideoElement provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLelement and HTMLMediaElement interfaces it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating video objects.

properties.name: height
properties.description: Reflects the height HTML attribute, which specifies the height of the display area, in CSS pixels.

properties.name: poster
properties.description: Reflects the poster HTML attribute, which specifies an image to show while no video data is available.

properties.name: videoHeight
properties.description: The intrinsic height of the resource in CSS pixels, taking into account the dimensions, aspect ratio, clean aperture, resolution, and so forth, as defined for the format used by the resource. If the element's ready state is HAVE_NOTHING, the value is 0.

properties.name: videoWidth
properties.description: The intrinsic width of the resource in CSS pixels, taking into account the dimensions, aspect ratio, clean aperture, resolution, and so forth, as defined for the format used by the resource. If the element's ready state is HAVE_NOTHING, the value is 0.

properties.name: width
properties.description: Reflects the width HTML attribute, which specifies the width of the display area, in CSS pixels.

name: IDBDatabaseException
description: In the IndexedDB API, an IDBDatabaseException object represents exception conditions that can be encountered while performing database operations.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The most appropriate error code for the condition.

properties.name: message
properties.description: Error message describing the exception raised.

name: IDBFactory
description: The IDBFactory interface of the IndexedDB API lets applications asynchronously access the indexed databases. The object that implements the interface is  window.indexedDB. You open—that is, create and access—and delete a database with the object and not directly with IDBFactory.

name: IDBIndex
description: The IDBIndex interface of the IndexedDB API provides asynchronous access to an index in a database. An index is a kind of object store for looking up records in another object store, called the referenced object store. You use this interface to retrieve data.

name: IDBKeyRange
description: The IDBKeyRange interface of the IndexedDB API represents a continuous interval over some data type that is used for keys. Records can be retrieved from object stores and indexes using keys or a range of keys. You can limit the range using lower and upper bounds. For example, you can iterate over all values of a key between x and y.

properties.name: upperOpen
properties.description: Returns false if the upper-bound value is included in the key range.

name: IDBRequest
description: The IDBRequest interface of the IndexedDB API provides access to results of asynchronous requests to databases and database objects using event handler attributes. Each reading and writing operation on a database is done using a request.

name: ImageData
description: Used with the <canvas> element. Returned by CanvasRenderingContext2D's createImageData and getImageData (and accepted as first argument in putImageData)

properties.name: width
properties.description: readonly unsigned long

properties.name: height
properties.description: readonly unsigned long

properties.name: data
properties.description: readonly Uint8ClampedArray data

name: KeyboardEvent
description: KeyboardEvent objects describe a user interaction with the keyboard. Each event describes a key; the event type (keydown, keypress, or keyup) identifies what kind of activity was performed.

properties.name: altKey
properties.description: true if the Alt (or Option, on Mac) key was active when the key event was generated. Read only.

properties.name: char
properties.description:
The character value of the key. If the key corresponds to a printable character, this value is a non-empty Unicode string containing that character. If the key doesn't have a printable representation, this is an empty string. See key names and char values for the detail. Read only.

Note: If the key is used as a macro that inserts multiple characters, this attribute's value is the entire string, not just the first character.

Gecko note: Not yet implemented; see bug 680830.

This attribute is not implemented in Gecko at this time.

properties.name: charCode
properties.description:
The Unicode reference number of the key; this attribute is used only by the keypress event. For keys whose char attribute contains multiple characters, this is the Unicode value of the first character in that attribute. Read only.

Warning: This attribute is deprecated; you should use char instead, if available.

properties.name: ctrlKey
properties.description: true if the Control key was active when the key event was generated. Read only.

properties.name: key
properties.description:
The key value of the key represented by the event. If the value has a printed representation, this attribute's value is the same as the char attribute. Otherwise, it's one of the key value strings specified in Key values. If the key can't be identified, this is the string "Unidentified". See key names and char values for the detail. Read only.

Gecko note: Not yet implemented; see bug 680830.

This attribute is not implemented in Gecko at this time.

properties.name: keyCode
properties.description:
A system and implementation dependent numerical code identifying the unmodified value of the pressed key. This is usually the decimal ASCII (

web.link("http://tools.ietf.org/html/" + $0, "RFC " + $0)

) or Windows 1252 code corresponding to the key; see Virtual key codes for a list of Gecko's keyCode values. If the key can't be identified, this value is 0. Read only.

Warning: This attribute is deprecated; you should use key instead, if available.

properties.name: locale
properties.description:
A locale string indicating the locale the keyboard is configured for. This may be the empty string if the browser or device doesn't know the keyboard's locale. Read only.

Note: This does not describe the locale of the data being entered. A user may be using one keyboard layout while typing text in a different language.

properties.name: location
properties.description: The location of the key on the keyboard or other input device; see Key location constants below. Read only.

properties.name: metaKey
properties.description: true if the Meta (or Command, on Mac) key was active when the key event was generated. Read only.

properties.name: repeat
properties.description:
true if the key is being held down such that it is automatically repeating. Read only.

Gecko note: Not yet implemented; see bug 600117.

This attribute is not implemented in Gecko at this time.

properties.name: shiftKey
properties.description: true if the Shift key was active when the key event was generated. Read only.

properties.name: which
properties.description:
A system and implementation dependent numeric code identifying the unmodified value of the pressed key; this is usually the same as keyCode. Read only.

Warning: This attribute is deprecated; you should use key instead, if available.

name: LinkStyle

properties.name: sheet
properties.description: Specifies the StyleSheet object associated with the given element.

name: LocalFileSystem
description: The LocalFileSystem interface of the File System API gives you access to a sandboxed file system.  The methods are implemented by window and worker objects.

name: LocalFileSystemSync
description: The LocalFileSystemSync interface of the File System API gives you access to a sandboxed file system. It is intended to be used with  WebWorkers. The methods are implemented by worker objects.

name: MediaQueryList
description: A MediaQueryList object maintains a list of media queries on a document, and handles sending notifications to listeners when the media queries on the document change.

properties.name: media

name: MediaQueryListListener
description: A MediaQueryList object maintains a list of media queries on a document, and handles sending notifications to listeners when the media queries on the document change.

name: MediaStream
description: The MediaStream interface represents a stream of media content. A stream consists of several tracks, like video or audio tracks.

properties.name: MediaStream.id
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing 36 characters denoting a unique identifier (GUID) for the object.

properties.name: MediaStream.ended
properties.description: Is a Boolean value with a value of true if the ended event has been fired on the object, meaning that the stream has been completely read, or false if the end of hte stream has not been reached.

name: MediaStreamTrack
description: The MediaStream interface represents a stream of media content. A stream consists of several tracks, like video or audio tracks.

properties.name: MediaStreamTrack.id
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a unique identifier (GUID) for the track; it is generated by the browser.

properties.name: MediaStreamTrack.kind
properties.description: Is a DOMString set to "audio" if the track is an audio track and to "video", if it is a video track. It doesn't change if the track is deassociate from its source.

properties.name: MediaStreamTrack.label
properties.description: Is a DOMString containing a user agent-assigned label that identifies the track source, as in "internal microphone". The string may be left empty and is empty as long as no source has been connected. When the track is deassociated from its source, the label is not changed.

properties.name: MediaStreamTrack.enabled
properties.description: Is a Boolean value with a value of true if the track is enabled, that is allowed to render the media source stream; or false if it is disabled, that is not rendering the media source stream but silence and blackness. If the track has been disconnected, this value can be changed but has no more effect.

properties.name: MediaStreamTrack.readyState
properties.description:
Is an enumerated value that gives the status of the track. It takes one of the following values:
  • "new" which is the original state and the track has not been connected to any source yet. In that state, the MediaStreamTrack.label will be the empty string. When a source is connected, the track state becomes "live" and an started is emitted.
  • "live" which indicates that an input is connected and does its best-effort in providing real-time data. In that case, the output of data can be switched on or off using the MediaStreamTrack.enabled attribute.
  • "ended"

name: MessageEvent
description: A MessageEvent is sent to clients using WebSockets when data is received from the server. This is delivered to the listener indicated by the WebSocket object's onmessage attribute.

properties.name: data
properties.description: The data from the server.

name: MouseEvent
description: The DOM MouseEvent interface represents events that occur due to the user interacting with a pointing device (such as a mouse).

properties.name: screenX
properties.description: The X coordinate of the mouse pointer in global (screen) coordinates. Read only.

properties.name: screenY
properties.description: The Y coordinate of the mouse pointer in global (screen) coordinates. Read only.

properties.name: clientX
properties.description: The X coordinate of the mouse pointer in local (DOM content) coordinates. Read only.

properties.name: clientY
properties.description: The Y coordinate of the mouse pointer in local (DOM content) coordinates. Read only.

properties.name: ctrlKey
properties.description: true if the control key was down when the mouse event was fired. Read only.

properties.name: shiftKey
properties.description: true if the shift key was down when the mouse event was fired. Read only.

properties.name: altKey
properties.description: true if the alt key was down when the mouse event was fired. Read only.

properties.name: metaKey
properties.description: true if the meta key was down when the mouse event was fired. Read only.

properties.name: button
properties.description:
The button number that was pressed when the mouse event was fired. Read only.

Left button=0, middle button=1 (if present), right button=2. For mice configured for left handed use in which the button actions are reversed the values are instead read from right to left.

properties.name: buttons
properties.description:
The buttons being pressed when the mouse event was fired. Read only.

Left button=1, Right button=2, Middle (wheel) button=4, 4th button (typically, "Browser Back" button)=8, 5th button (typically, "Browser Forward" button)=16. If two or more buttons are pressed, returns the logical sum of the values. E.g., if Left button and Right button are pressed, returns 3 (=1 | 2).

Gecko supports this attribute on Windows, Linux (GTK) and Mac.

  • On Windows, if user installed a mouse driver and its utility software which can customize button actions (e.g., IntelliPoint and SetPoint), the Middle (wheel) button, 4th button and 5th button may not be set actually even when they're pressed.
  • On Linux (GTK), 4th button and 5th button are not supported. And also, mouseup event always have the releasing button information in this attribute value.
  • On Mac OS X 10.5, buttons attribute always returns 0 because there is no platform API for implementing this feature.

properties.name: relatedTarget
properties.description:
The secondary target for the event, if there is one. Read only.

For mouseenter/mouseleave, mouseover/mouseout events an event's relatedTarget equals the Event.target of the complementary event. For example, the relatedTarget for mouseleave is the target for the corresponding mouseenter event.

For events with no secondary target, relatedTarget returns null.

properties.name: mozPressure
properties.description: The amount of pressure applied to a touch or tablet device when generating the event; this value ranges between 0.0 (minimum pressure) and 1.0 (maximum pressure). Read only.

properties.name: mozInputSource
properties.description:
The type of device that generated the event (one of the MOZ_SOURCE_* constants listed below). Read only.

This lets you, for example, determine whether a mouse event was generated by an actual mouse or by a touch event (which might affect the degree of accuracy with which you interpret the coordinates associated with the event).

name: MouseScrollEvent
description: The DOM MouseScrollEvent represents events that occur due to the user moving a mouse wheel or similar input device.

properties.name: axis
properties.description: Indicates scroll direction. Read only.

name: MouseWheelEvent
description: The DOM MouseWheelEvent represents events that occur due to the user turning a mouse wheel.

properties.name: wheelDelta
properties.description: The distance in pixels (defined as so by MSDN, but the actual usage is different, see mousewheel). Read only.

name: MozActivity
description: The MozActivity interface allows apps to delegate an activity to another app.

name: MozActivityOptions
description: The MozActivityOptions interface allows apps to declare the activity they want to create and also to access information of activities they want to handle.

properties.name: MozActivityOptions.data

name: MozActivityRequestHandler

properties.name: MozActivityRequestHandler.source
properties.description: A MozActivityOptions object containing all the information about the current activity request.

name: MozAlarmsManager

properties.name: MozMobileCellInfo.gsmLocationAreaCode

properties.name: MozMobileConnection.oniccinfochange

properties.name: MozMobileConnection.onussdreceived

name: MutationObserver
description: MutationObserver provides developers a way to react to changes in a DOM. It is designed as a replacement for Mutation Events defined in the DOM3 Events specification.

name: NamedNodeMap
description: A collection of nodes returned by Element.attributes (also potentially for DocumentType.entities, DocumentType.notations). NamedNodeMaps are not in any particular order (unlike NodeList), although they may be accessed by an index as in an array (they may also be accessed with the item() method). A NamedNodeMap object are live and will thus be auto-updated if changes are made to their contents internally or elsewhere.

name: NameList
description: Provides an abstraction for an ordered collection of name and namespace value pairs. Items can be accessed by a 0-based index. The DOM spec does not specify how the collection is to be implemented.

name: Node
